n for \"half\"?","o":["2/1","1/2","2/2","1/4"],"a":1,"e":"Half=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Candy bar split in 3 equal pieces, eat 1. Fraction?<svg width=\"180\" height=\"55\" viewBox=\"0 0 180 55\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"15\" y=\"5\" width=\"150\" height=\"42\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#6E2F0A\" stroke=\"#4A1C03\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><rect x=\"17\" y=\"7\" width=\"146\" height=\"8\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\"/><rect x=\"17.0\" y=\"9\" width=\"44.7\" height=\"32\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"#F39C12\"/><rect x=\"17.0\" y=\"9\" width=\"44.7\" height=\"32\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#E67E22\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"40.3\" cy=\"25\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C1503\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><rect x=\"63.7\" y=\"9\" width=\"44.7\" height=\"32\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"#784212\"/><circle cx=\"87.0\" cy=\"25\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C1503\" opacity=\"0.7\"/><rect x=\"110.3\" y=\"9\" width=\"44.7\" height=\"32\" rx=\"3\" fill=\"#784212\"/><circle cx=\"133.7\" cy=\"25\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C1503\" opacity=\"0.7\"/></svg>","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","3/1"],"a":1,"e":"1 of 3=1/3.","d":"h"},{"t":"5/5 = ?","o":["5 halves","1 whole","5 wholes","1/5"],"a":1,"e":"5 of 5=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Shape divided in 4 parts — 2 are equal, 2 are not. Valid fraction?","o":["Yes","No","Maybe","Depends"],"a":1,"e":"Parts must ALL be equal for a valid fraction.","d":"m"},{"t":"Numerator of 3/7?","o":["7","3","10","4"],"a":1,"e":"Top number=3=numerator.","d":"e"},{"t":"Denominator of 5/8?","o":["5","8","13","3"],"a":1,"e":"Bottom number=8=denominator.","d":"m"},{"t":"6 equal parts, 6 colored. Fraction = ?","o":["0/6","1/6","6/6","6/0"],"a":2,"e":"All 6 colored=6/6=1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is a fraction?","o":["3+4","7-2","2/5","3×1"],"a":2,"e":"2/5 is a fraction.","d":"e"},{"t":"Fraction for \"three fourths\"?","o":["3/7","4/3","3/4","7/3"],"a":2,"e":"Three fourths=3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Watermelon cut into 8 equal slices, 3 eaten. Left?<svg width=\"110\" height=\"110\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"44\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#E74C3C\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"20\" fill=\"#F1948A\" opacity=\"0.4\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.0,6.0 A44,44,0,0,1,81.1,18.9 Z\" fill=\"#f0f0f0\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.0,6.0 A44,44,0,0,1,81.1,18.9 Z\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L81.1,18.9 A44,44,0,0,1,94.0,50.0 Z\" fill=\"#f0f0f0\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L81.1,18.9 A44,44,0,0,1,94.0,50.0 Z\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L94.0,50.0 A44,44,0,0,1,81.1,81.1 Z\" fill=\"#f0f0f0\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L94.0,50.0 A44,44,0,0,1,81.1,81.1 Z\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,2\"/><circle cx=\"35\" cy=\"38\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"55\" cy=\"32\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"65\" cy=\"55\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"68\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"62\" cy=\"68\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"38\" cy=\"62\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"42\" r=\"2\" fill=\"#2C3E50\" opacity=\"0.6\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.0\" y2=\"6.0\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"81.1\" y2=\"18.9\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"94.0\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"81.1\" y2=\"81.1\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.0\" y2=\"94.0\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"18.9\" y2=\"81.1\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"6.0\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"18.9\" y2=\"18.9\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"44\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#1e8449\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["3/8","5/8","8/5","8/3"],"a":1,"e":"8-3=5 left. 5/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"4 parts, 1 shaded. Fraction?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"54\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 54\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"95.0\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">1 out of 4 parts</text></svg>","o":["4/1","1/4","1/1","4/4"],"a":1,"e":"1 of 4=1/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many thirds in 1 whole?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":1,"e":"3/3=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"10 equal parts, 7 colored. Fraction?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"54\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 54\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"19.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"38.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"57.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"76.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"114.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"133.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"152.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"171.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"19.0\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"95.0\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">7 out of 10 parts</text></svg>","o":["7/10","10/7","3/10","10/3"],"a":0,"e":"7 of 10=7/10.","d":"h"},{"t":"8 cookies shared equally among 2 friends. How many does each friend get?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":2,"e":"8 ÷ 2 = 4 cookies each. Equal sharing!","d":"m"},{"t":"A pizza has 4 equal slices. You eat 1 slice. How many are left?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":2,"e":"4 − 1 = 3 slices left.","d":"m"},{"t":"You have 2 halves of one sandwich and 2 halves of another. How many whole sandwiches?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves = 1 whole. So 2 + 2 halves = 2 wholes.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pizza is cut into 2 equal slices. What is each slice called?","o":["A fourth","A half","An eighth","A whole"],"a":1,"e":"When you split something into 2 equal parts, each part is called a half.","d":"e"},{"t":"A sandwich is cut into 4 equal pieces. What is each piece called?","o":["A half","A whole","A fourth","An eighth"],"a":2,"e":"When something is split into 4 equal parts, each part is called a fourth (or a quarter).","d":"e"},{"t":"A circle is split into 2 equal parts. 1 part is shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/4","1/2","2/2","1/8"],"a":1,"e":"There are 2 equal parts and 1 is shaded, so the fraction is 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 4 equal parts. 1 part is colored blue. What fraction is blue?","o":["1/2","4/4","1/4","4/1"],"a":2,"e":"There are 4 equal parts and 1 is colored. That is 1 out of 4, or 1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"What does the bottom number in a fraction tell you?","o":["How many parts are shaded","How many equal parts in all","How many are left over","How big the shape is"],"a":1,"e":"The bottom number tells how many equal parts the whole is divided into.","d":"e"},{"t":"What does the top number in a fraction tell you?","o":["How many equal parts in all","How many parts we are talking about","How big each part is","How many wholes there are"],"a":1,"e":"The top number tells how many of the equal parts we are counting.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 8 equal slices. What is each slice called?","o":["A half","A fourth","An eighth","A whole"],"a":2,"e":"When something is split into 8 equal parts, each part is called an eighth.","d":"m"},{"t":"A square is split into 4 equal parts. All 4 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/4","4/4","4/1","0/4"],"a":1,"e":"All 4 out of 4 parts are shaded, so the fraction is 4/4. That equals 1 whole!","d":"m"},{"t":"In the fraction 3/8, what does the 8 mean?","o":["3 parts are shaded","The whole has 8 equal parts","There are 8 shapes","You ate 8 pieces"],"a":1,"e":"The bottom number 8 tells you the whole is split into 8 equal parts.","d":"m"},{"t":"In the fraction 3/8, what does the 3 mean?","o":["There are 3 equal parts in all","The shape has 3 sides","We are counting 3 of the parts","There are 3 shapes"],"a":2,"e":"The top number 3 means we are counting 3 of the 8 equal parts.","d":"m"},{"t":"A circle is split into 8 equal parts. 3 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["3/8","8/3","3/3","1/8"],"a":0,"e":"3 parts out of 8 equal parts are shaded. The fraction is 3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"A waffle is cut into 4 equal squares. You eat 3 of them. What fraction did you eat?","o":["3/4","4/3","1/4","3/3"],"a":0,"e":"You ate 3 out of 4 equal parts. That is the fraction 3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which of these is a fraction?","o":["5 + 3","1/4","12","A square"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 is a fraction. It has a top number and a bottom number separated by a line.","d":"e"},{"t":"A cookie is split into 2 equal parts. You eat 1 part. What fraction did you eat?","o":["1/2","2/1","1/4","2/2"],"a":0,"e":"You ate 1 out of 2 equal parts. That is 1/2 of the cookie.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 2 equal parts. 0 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["2/2","1/2","0/2","2/0"],"a":2,"e":"No parts are shaded out of 2 equal parts, so the fraction is 0/2. That means zero!","d":"m"},{"t":"What must be true about the parts to write a fraction?","o":["They must be different sizes","They must be equal","There must be only 2 parts","The shape must be a circle"],"a":1,"e":"To write a fraction, the whole must be split into equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"A fruit bar has 4 equal pieces. You give away 2 pieces. What fraction did you give away?","o":["4/2","2/4","1/4","2/2"],"a":1,"e":"You gave away 2 out of 4 equal pieces. That is 2/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many fourths make 1 whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"It takes 4 fourths to make 1 whole. Think of 4 puzzle pieces making a full picture!","d":"e"},{"t":"If a shape has 8 equal parts and 1 is shaded, what fraction is shaded?","o":["8/1","1/1","1/8","8/8"],"a":2,"e":"1 part out of 8 equal parts is shaded. The fraction is 1/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"A cracker is broken into 2 equal parts. What fraction is 1 part?","o":["2/1","1/2","1/4","2/2"],"a":1,"e":"1 part out of 2 equal parts is 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is split into 4 parts, but the parts are NOT equal. Can you write a fraction for the shaded part?","o":["Yes, because there are 4 parts","No, because the parts must be equal","Yes, because part is shaded","No, because there are too many parts"],"a":1,"e":"Fractions only work when the parts are equal. If the parts are different sizes, we cannot write a fraction.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which shows 1/4?","o":["1 out of 3 equal parts shaded","1 out of 4 equal parts shaded","4 out of 1 part shaded","4 out of 4 equal parts shaded"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 means 1 out of 4 equal parts. The bottom number tells how many equal parts, and the top tells how many are shaded.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many eighths make 1 whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"It takes 8 eighths (8/8) to make 1 whole. You need all 8 pieces to complete the whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A brownie is cut into 8 equal pieces. Maria eats 2 pieces. What fraction of the brownie is left?","o":["2/8","6/8","8/2","8/6"],"a":1,"e":"Maria ate 2 of 8 pieces, so 8 - 2 = 6 pieces are left. That is 6/8 of the brownie.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is divided into parts. 3 parts are big and 1 part is small. Can we say 1/4 is shaded if the small part is colored?","o":["Yes, because there are 4 parts","No, because the parts are not equal","Yes, because 1 part is shaded","No, because rectangles cannot show fractions"],"a":1,"e":"We cannot write 1/4 because the parts are not equal. Fractions require equal-sized parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo shades 2/4 of a square. Mia shades 1/2 of the same size square. Who shaded more?","o":["Leo shaded more","Mia shaded more","They shaded the same amount","You cannot compare them"],"a":2,"e":"2/4 and 1/2 are the same amount! If you shade 2 out of 4 equal parts, that is the same as 1 out of 2 equal parts.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pizza has 8 equal slices. 4 slices have pepperoni. What fraction has pepperoni?","o":["8/4","4/4","4/8","1/4"],"a":2,"e":"4 out of 8 equal slices have pepperoni. That is the fraction 4/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which fraction is the same as 1 whole?","o":["1/2","2/4","4/4","3/4"],"a":2,"e":"4/4 means all 4 parts out of 4 are counted. That is the whole thing, or 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Jake says 3/4 means 4 out of 3 equal parts. Is Jake correct?","o":["Yes, that is right","No, it means 3 out of 4 equal parts","No, it means 3 wholes and 4 parts","Yes, the bigger number always goes on top"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 means 3 out of 4 equal parts. The top number (3) is how many we count, and the bottom (4) is how many equal parts in all.","d":"m"},{"t":"A granola bar is split into 4 equal parts. You eat some and 1/4 is left. How many parts did you eat?","o":["1 part","2 parts","3 parts","4 parts"],"a":2,"e":"If 1/4 is left, that means 1 out of 4 parts remains. So you ate the other 3 parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is split into 8 equal parts. How many parts do you need to shade to show 1/2?","o":["1 part","2 parts","4 parts","8 parts"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8 is 4, so you shade 4 out of 8 parts to show 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Amy has a ribbon cut into 8 equal pieces. She uses 5 pieces. What fraction did she NOT use?","o":["5/8","3/8","8/5","8/3"],"a":1,"e":"She used 5 out of 8, so 8 - 5 = 3 pieces are not used. That is 3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which two fractions are equal to 1 whole?","o":["1/2 and 2/4","2/2 and 8/8","1/4 and 1/8","3/4 and 4/8"],"a":1,"e":"2/2 = 1 whole and 8/8 = 1 whole. Whenever the top and bottom numbers are the same, it equals 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"There are 4 equal boxes. 2 are red and 2 are blue. What fraction is red?","o":["2/2","4/2","2/4","1/2"],"a":2,"e":"2 out of 4 equal boxes are red. The fraction is 2/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Kai splits a cracker into 2 pieces, but one piece is much bigger than the other. He says each piece is 1/2. Is Kai correct?","o":["Yes, because there are 2 pieces","No, because the pieces are not equal","Yes, because he split it in half","No, because crackers cannot be fractions"],"a":1,"e":"Kai is wrong. For each piece to be 1/2, the two pieces must be equal in size.","d":"m"},{"t":"A shape is split into 8 equal parts. ___ out of 8 parts are shaded to show 7/8. What number fills the blank?","o":["1","7","8","6"],"a":1,"e":"7/8 means 7 out of 8 equal parts. So the blank is 7.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pancake is cut into 4 equal slices. You eat 1 slice. What fraction of the pancake is left?","o":["1/4","4/4","3/4","2/4"],"a":2,"e":"You started with 4/4. After eating 1 slice, 4 - 1 = 3 slices remain. That is 3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Sara says 0/4 means nothing is shaded. Is she correct?","o":["Yes, 0 out of 4 parts means none are shaded","No, 0/4 is not a real fraction","No, it means all parts are shaded","Yes, but only for circles"],"a":0,"e":"Sara is correct! 0/4 means 0 parts out of 4 are shaded -- that is none at all.","d":"e"},{"t":"A rectangle has ___ equal parts. 3 are shaded. The fraction is 3/4. How many equal parts does the rectangle have?","o":["3","4","7","8"],"a":1,"e":"In 3/4, the bottom number is 4. That means the rectangle is split into 4 equal parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"Sam says 1/4 is bigger than 1/2 because 4 is bigger than 2. Is Sam correct?","o":["Yes, because 4 > 2","No, because more parts means each part is smaller","Yes, because fourths are bigger than halves","No, because you cannot compare fractions"],"a":1,"e":"Sam is wrong. When you cut something into MORE pieces, each piece gets SMALLER. So 1/4 is smaller than 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Emma ate 2/8 of a pizza. Jake ate 3/8 of the same pizza. How much did they eat together? Is more than half the pizza gone?","o":["5/8 -- yes, more than half is gone","5/8 -- no, less than half is gone","5/16 -- yes, more than half is gone","6/8 -- yes, more than half is gone"],"a":0,"e":"2/8 + 3/8 = 5/8. Half the pizza is 4/8. Since 5/8 > 4/8, yes, more than half is gone!","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 5 fourths of a pie. Is that more or less than 1 whole pie?","o":["Less than 1 whole","Exactly 1 whole","More than 1 whole by 1/4","You cannot have 5 fourths"],"a":2,"e":"4/4 = 1 whole. 5/4 means you have 1 whole pie plus 1/4 more. That is more than 1 whole!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 6 parts. 2 parts are big and 4 parts are small. Can you say 4/6 of the rectangle is shaded if the 4 small parts are colored?","o":["Yes, because 4 of 6 parts are colored","No, because the parts are not equal","Yes, because most parts are colored","No, because rectangles only split into 4 parts"],"a":1,"e":"You cannot write 4/6 because the parts are not equal. Fractions require all parts to be the same size.","d":"h"},{"t":"3 friends share 2 pies equally. What fraction of a pie does each friend get?","o":["1/3","2/3","3/2","1/2"],"a":1,"e":"2 pies shared among 3 friends = 2/3 per friend. Each person gets 2 thirds of a pie.","d":"m"},{"t":"Mia says 2/4 of her cookie is the same as 1/2. Is Mia correct? Why?","o":["No, because 2 and 1 are different numbers","Yes, because both show the same amount of cookie","No, because 4 is bigger than 2","Yes, but only if the cookie is round"],"a":1,"e":"Mia is correct! 2 out of 4 equal parts is the same amount as 1 out of 2 equal parts. They are equal fractions.","d":"m"},{"t":"A cake has 8 equal slices. Ben eats 3 slices and Zara eats 2 slices. What fraction of the cake is LEFT?","o":["5/8","3/8","6/8","2/8"],"a":1,"e":"Ben ate 3 and Zara ate 2. That is 3 + 2 = 5 slices eaten. 8 - 5 = 3 slices left. The answer is 3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Liam says 8/8 is bigger than 4/4. Is he right?","o":["Yes, because 8 is bigger than 4","No, they are both equal to 1 whole","Yes, because eighths are bigger than fourths","No, 4/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"8/8 = 1 whole and 4/4 = 1 whole. They are the same! When the top and bottom are equal, it always means 1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"You cut a ribbon into 4 equal pieces. You use 3 pieces for a gift and then cut another equal ribbon into 4 pieces. How many fourths do you have in total now?","o":["3 fourths","4 fourths","5 fourths","7 fourths"],"a":2,"e":"From the first ribbon you have 1 fourth left. The second ribbon gives you 4 fourths. 1 + 4 = 5 fourths total.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is split into 8 equal parts. 4 parts are red and 2 are blue. What fraction is NOT colored?","o":["6/8","4/8","2/8","8/8"],"a":2,"e":"Red uses 4 parts and blue uses 2. That is 4 + 2 = 6 colored parts. 8 - 6 = 2 are not colored. The answer is 2/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Nora says you cannot have a fraction bigger than 1 whole. Is she correct?","o":["Yes, fractions are always less than 1","No, fractions like 5/4 are more than 1 whole","Yes, the top number must be smaller","No, but only with eighths"],"a":1,"e":"Nora is wrong! Fractions like 5/4 or 3/2 are bigger than 1 whole. The top number CAN be larger than the bottom.","d":"m"},{"t":"Max ate 1/4 of a pizza on Monday and 2/4 on Tuesday. What fraction has he eaten in total? What fraction is left?","o":["3/4 eaten, 1/4 left","3/8 eaten, 5/8 left","2/4 eaten, 2/4 left","3/4 eaten, 3/4 left"],"a":0,"e":"1/4 + 2/4 = 3/4 eaten. The whole pizza is 4/4, so 4/4 - 3/4 = 1/4 is left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava splits a candy bar into 8 equal pieces. She gives 1/2 of the bar to her brother. How many pieces did she give him?","o":["2 pieces","4 pieces","1 piece","8 pieces"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 8 pieces is 4 pieces. So 1/2 of the candy bar = 4/8 = 4 pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"A teacher splits a paper into 4 equal parts. She colors 2 parts red and 1 part blue. She says 3/4 is colored. A student says only 2/4 is colored because the colors are different. Who is right?","o":["The teacher, because 2 + 1 = 3 parts are colored","The student, because different colors do not count together","Neither -- the answer is 1/4","Both are right"],"a":0,"e":"The teacher is right. 2 red + 1 blue = 3 colored parts out of 4. It does not matter that the colors are different -- 3/4 is colored.","d":"h"},{"t":"2 friends share 1 pie equally. Then 1 more friend arrives and they start over, sharing 1 pie equally among 3. Does each person get more or less pie now?","o":["More, because there are more friends","Less, because the pie is split into more pieces","The same amount","You cannot share a pie among 3"],"a":1,"e":"With 2 friends each gets 1/2. With 3 friends each gets 1/3. 1/3 < 1/2, so each person gets LESS pie.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kai colors 6/8 of a rectangle. Lily colors 3/4 of the same size rectangle. Who colored more?","o":["Kai colored more","Lily colored more","They colored the same amount","You cannot compare them"],"a":2,"e":"6/8 and 3/4 are equal! 3/4 = 6/8 because if you split each fourth into 2 parts, 3 fourths become 6 eighths.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pan of brownies has 8 equal pieces. Mom eats 1/8, Dad eats 2/8, and you eat 3/8. How much is left for your sister?","o":["6/8","3/8","2/8","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 + 2/8 + 3/8 = 6/8 eaten. 8/8 - 6/8 = 2/8 is left for your sister.","d":"h"},{"t":"Tom says 0/8 and 0/4 are different amounts because 8 and 4 are different. Is Tom right?","o":["Yes, because the bottom numbers are different","No, both equal zero -- nothing is shaded","Yes, 0/8 is bigger","No, 0/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"Tom is wrong. 0/8 = 0 and 0/4 = 0. Zero parts shaded is always zero, no matter how many parts the whole has.","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 3 halves of a sandwich. How many whole sandwiches is that?","o":["1 whole","1 whole and 1 half","2 wholes","3 wholes"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves = 1 whole. You have 3 halves, so that is 1 whole sandwich plus 1/2 more.","d":"e"},{"t":"Zoe says if you cut a pizza into more slices, you get more pizza. Is she correct?","o":["Yes, more slices means more pizza","No, the pizza is the same size no matter how you cut it","Yes, but only if the slices are equal","No, you actually get less pizza"],"a":1,"e":"Zoe is wrong. Cutting a pizza into more slices does not create more pizza. The total amount stays the same -- each slice is just smaller.","d":"e"}],"quiz":[{"t":"Pizza cut into 4 equal slices. You eat 1. Fraction?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1 slice out of 4 equal slices = 1/4."},{"t":"Bottom number of a fraction is called?","o":["Numerator","Denominator","Whole","Total"],"a":1,"e":"Denominator (bottom) = total number of equal parts."},{"t":"Top number of a fraction is called?","o":["Denominator","Numerator","Whole","Parts"],"a":1,"e":"Numerator (top) = how many parts you have."},{"t":"For a fraction to be valid, parts must be?","o":["Any size","Equal size","Different sizes","3 or more"],"a":1,"e":"All parts MUST be the same equal size."},{"t":"Ribbon cut into 8 equal pieces, you use 3. Fraction?","o":["3/5","5/8","3/8","8/3"],"a":2,"e":"3 out of 8 equal pieces = 3/8."},{"t":"4/4 = ?","o":["Zero parts","One half","1 whole","2 wholes"],"a":2,"e":"All 4 parts out of 4 total = 1 complete whole."}]},{"points":["1/2 = one half (2 equal parts, one shaded)","1/4 = one fourth (4 equal parts, one shaded)","1/8 = one eighth (8 equal parts, one shaded)","MORE equal parts = SMALLER each piece!","1/2 > 1/4 > 1/8"],"examples":[{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Common Fractions","p":"From largest to smallest piece:","s":"<div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,50.00,90.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">2</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e74c3c;font-size:13px\">one half</div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e67e22;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">4</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e67e22;font-size:13px\">one fourth</div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#f3eaf8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,21.72 Z\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#8e44ad;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#8e44ad\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" font-weight=\"bold\">8</text></svg><div style=\"color:#8e44ad;font-size:13px\">one eighth</div></div></div></div>","a":"1/2 is the biggest piece, 1/8 is the smallest ✅"},{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Key Rule","p":"Why is 1/8 smaller than 1/2?","s":"<div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#555;margin:6px 0\">More equal cuts - each piece gets <b>smaller</b>!</div><div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/4</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e67e22;margin-top:4px\">4 pieces - bigger slice</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#f3eaf8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,21.72 Z\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/8</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#8e44ad;margin-top:4px\">8 pieces - smaller slice!</div></div></div>","a":"More cuts = smaller pieces ✅"},{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Practice","p":"Pie with 8 equal slices:","s":"<div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"80\" height=\"80\" viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L40.00,8.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,17.37 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"8.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"72.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"72.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"8.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\">1 slice = 1/8</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"80\" height=\"80\" viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L40.00,8.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,17.37 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L62.63,17.37 A32,32,0,0,1,72.00,40.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"8.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"72.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"72.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"8.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\">2 slices = 2/8</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"80\" height=\"80\" viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L40.00,8.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,17.37 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L62.63,17.37 A32,32,0,0,1,72.00,40.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L72.00,40.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,62.63 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L62.63,62.63 A32,32,0,0,1,40.00,72.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"8.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"72.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"72.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"8.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\">4 slices = 4/8</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"80\" height=\"80\" viewBox=\"0 0 80 80\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"40\" cy=\"40\" r=\"32\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L40.00,8.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,17.37 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L62.63,17.37 A32,32,0,0,1,72.00,40.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L72.00,40.00 A32,32,0,0,1,62.63,62.63 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L62.63,62.63 A32,32,0,0,1,40.00,72.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L40.00,72.00 A32,32,0,0,1,17.37,62.63 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L17.37,62.63 A32,32,0,0,1,8.00,40.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L8.00,40.00 A32,32,0,0,1,17.37,17.37 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M40,40 L17.37,17.37 A32,32,0,0,1,40.00,8.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"8.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"17.37\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"72.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"62.63\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"40.00\" y2=\"72.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"62.63\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"8.00\" y2=\"40.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"40\" y1=\"40\" x2=\"17.37\" y2=\"17.37\" 