"44\" fill=\"#F0B27A\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"36\" fill=\"#E74C3C\"/><ellipse cx=\"35\" cy=\"30\" rx=\"9\" ry=\"6\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"63\" cy=\"35\" rx=\"10\" ry=\"6\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"33\" cy=\"60\" rx=\"7\" ry=\"8\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"63\" cy=\"60\" rx=\"8\" ry=\"7\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"50\" cy=\"71\" rx=\"7\" ry=\"5\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><circle cx=\"38\" cy=\"32\" r=\"4.5\" fill=\"#922B21\" stroke=\"#7B241C\" stroke-width=\"0.5\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"63\" cy=\"40\" r=\"4.5\" fill=\"#922B21\" stroke=\"#7B241C\" stroke-width=\"0.5\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"36\" cy=\"63\" r=\"4.5\" fill=\"#922B21\" stroke=\"#7B241C\" stroke-width=\"0.5\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"64\" cy=\"63\" r=\"4.5\" fill=\"#922B21\" stroke=\"#7B241C\" stroke-width=\"0.5\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.0,6.0 A44,44,0,0,1,94.0,50.0 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.0,6.0 A44,44,0,0,1,94.0,50.0 Z\" fill=\"rgba(39,174,96,0.35)\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L94.0,50.0 A44,44,0,0,1,50.0,94.0 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L94.0,50.0 A44,44,0,0,1,50.0,94.0 Z\" fill=\"rgba(39,174,96,0.35)\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.0\" y2=\"6.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"94.0\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.0\" y2=\"94.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"6.0\" y2=\"50.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"44\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/2"],"a":1,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Rectangle: 8 parts, 4 shaded. Fraction?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"54\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 54\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"95.0\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">4 out of 8 parts</text></svg>","o":["1/8","2/8","3/8","4/8"],"a":3,"e":"4/8=1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"3/8 is?","o":["3 wholes and 8 parts","3 parts out of 8","8 parts out of 3","3 plus 8 parts"],"a":1,"e":"3 of 8 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"More than half: 3/4 or 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/4","Equal","Neither"],"a":1,"e":"3/4>1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is closest to 1 whole?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","3/4"],"a":3,"e":"3/4 is largest — closest to 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"7/8 means how many parts shaded?","o":["1","7","8","15"],"a":1,"e":"7 out of 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Fold paper in 4 equal parts, color 1. Fraction colored?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"54\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 54\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"47.5\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"95.0\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">1 out of 4 parts</text></svg>","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","4/1"],"a":2,"e":"1 of 4=1/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"2/8 is same as?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","3/8"],"a":1,"e":"2/8=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which shows one half?","o":["2/4","1/4","3/4","2/8"],"a":0,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Bar split in 8 equal parts, 6 colored. Fraction?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"54\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 54\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><text x=\"95.0\" y=\"51\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">6 out of 8 parts</text></svg>","o":["5/8","6/8","7/8","8/6"],"a":1,"e":"6/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Less than half: 1/8, 3/4, 1/2, 5/8?","o":["3/4","5/8","1/2","1/8"],"a":3,"e":"1/8<1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Circle divided into 4. 3 parts colored. Fraction?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/3"],"a":2,"e":"3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"5/8 + 3/8 = ?","o":["7/8","8/8","1 whole","8/16"],"a":2,"e":"5+3=8. 8/8=1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is half of 1/2?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/3","1/6"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 1/2=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Shade 3/8 of 8 equal parts. How many colored?","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":1,"e":"3 out of 8=3 colored.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/4 + 1/4 = ?","o":["1/4","1/2","3/4","1"],"a":1,"e":"1+1=2 fourths=2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"5/8 − 2/8 = ?","o":["2/8","3/8","4/8","5/8"],"a":1,"e":"5-2=3. 3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"4/4 − 1/4 = ?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":2,"e":"4-1=3. 3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/8 + 4/8 = ?","o":["4/8","6/8","8/8","10/8"],"a":1,"e":"2+4=6. 6/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/2 of 8 = ?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8=4.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 4 equal parts. 1 part is shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","4/4"],"a":1,"e":"1 out of 4 equal parts is shaded. That is the fraction 1/4, or one fourth.","d":"e"},{"t":"A circle is cut into 2 equal parts. What is each part called?","o":["A fourth","An eighth","A half","A whole"],"a":2,"e":"When a shape is cut into 2 equal parts, each part is called a half.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 8 equal slices. 5 slices are eaten. What fraction was eaten?","o":["5/8","8/5","3/8","5/5"],"a":0,"e":"5 out of 8 equal slices were eaten. The fraction is 5/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many halves make 1 whole?","o":["1","2","4","8"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves put together make 1 whole. Think of 2 half-circles making a full circle.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many fourths make 1 whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":1,"e":"4 fourths make 1 whole. 4/4 = 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many eighths make 1 whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"8 eighths make 1 whole. 8/8 = 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A square is split into 2 equal parts. Both parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/2","2/2","2/1","0/2"],"a":1,"e":"Both parts are shaded, so 2 out of 2 parts are shaded. That is 2/2, or 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A candy bar is split into 8 equal pieces. You eat 1 piece. What fraction did you eat?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","8/1"],"a":2,"e":"You ate 1 out of 8 equal pieces. That is 1/8 of the candy bar.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is cut into 4 equal parts. 3 parts are colored green. What fraction is green?","o":["1/4","3/4","4/3","3/3"],"a":1,"e":"3 out of 4 equal parts are green. The fraction is 3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pizza is cut into 2 equal slices. 1 slice has pepperoni. What fraction has pepperoni?","o":["2/1","1/2","2/2","1/1"],"a":1,"e":"1 out of 2 equal slices has pepperoni. That is 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A circle is split into 8 equal parts. 0 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["8/8","1/8","0/8","8/0"],"a":2,"e":"No parts are shaded, so 0 out of 8 are shaded. That is 0/8, which means none.","d":"m"},{"t":"A waffle is cut into 4 equal pieces. You eat 2. What fraction is left?","o":["2/4","4/4","1/4","3/4"],"a":0,"e":"You ate 2 out of 4 pieces, so 4 - 2 = 2 pieces are left. That is 2/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction means the whole shape is shaded?","o":["0/4","1/4","2/4","4/4"],"a":3,"e":"4/4 means all 4 parts out of 4 are shaded. That is the whole shape!","d":"e"},{"t":"An apple is cut into 4 equal slices. Your friend takes 1 slice. What fraction does your friend have?","o":["1/4","4/1","1/2","3/4"],"a":0,"e":"Your friend took 1 out of 4 equal slices. That is 1/4 of the apple.","d":"m"},{"t":"A ribbon is cut into 8 equal pieces. 7 pieces are red. What fraction is red?","o":["1/8","7/8","8/7","7/7"],"a":1,"e":"7 out of 8 equal pieces are red. The fraction is 7/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"A paper is folded into 2 equal parts. You color 1 part. What fraction is colored?","o":["2/1","1/4","1/2","2/2"],"a":2,"e":"1 out of 2 equal parts is colored. That is 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A square is cut into 4 equal parts. 4 parts are colored. What fraction is NOT colored?","o":["4/4","0/4","1/4","3/4"],"a":1,"e":"All 4 parts are colored, so 0 parts are not colored. That is 0/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"A cracker is broken into 2 equal halves. What fraction is each half?","o":["1/2","2/2","1/4","1/8"],"a":0,"e":"Each half is 1 out of 2 equal parts. That is 1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"A circle is divided into 8 equal parts. 4 parts are shaded yellow. What fraction is yellow?","o":["8/4","1/8","4/4","4/8"],"a":3,"e":"4 out of 8 equal parts are yellow. The fraction is 4/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 4 equal parts. 2 parts are blue. What fraction is NOT blue?","o":["2/4","4/4","1/4","3/4"],"a":0,"e":"2 parts are blue, so 4 - 2 = 2 parts are not blue. That is 2/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"A circle is divided into 4 equal parts. How many parts do you shade to show 1/2?","o":["1 part","2 parts","3 parts","4 parts"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 4 is 2. So you shade 2 out of 4 equal parts to show 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 8 equal parts. You shade 4 parts. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/8","4/8","8/4","1/4"],"a":1,"e":"4 out of 8 equal parts are shaded. That is 4/8, which is the same as 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 1 half or 1 fourth?","o":["1 fourth, because 4 > 2","1 half, because fewer pieces means bigger pieces","They are the same","You cannot compare them"],"a":1,"e":"1 half is bigger. When you cut into fewer pieces, each piece is larger. Half > fourth.","d":"e"},{"t":"Tina has a pie cut into 8 equal slices. She eats 3 slices. What fraction of the pie is LEFT?","o":["3/8","8/3","5/8","6/8"],"a":2,"e":"She ate 3 of 8 slices. 8 - 3 = 5 slices are left. That is 5/8 of the pie.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many eighths equal 1/2?","o":["2 eighths","4 eighths","6 eighths","8 eighths"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 8 is 4. So 4/8 = 1/2. Four eighths equal one half.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pizza has 4 equal slices. Carlos eats 1 slice and gives 1 slice to his sister. What fraction of the pizza is left?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":1,"e":"Carlos ate 1 and gave away 1. That is 2 slices gone. 4 - 2 = 2 slices left. That is 2/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which fraction equals 1 whole: 2/2, 2/4, or 2/8?","o":["2/2","2/4","2/8","All of them"],"a":0,"e":"2/2 means 2 out of 2 equal parts -- that is the whole thing. 2/4 and 2/8 are less than 1 whole.","d":"h"},{"t":"Maya says 2/8 and 1/4 are the same amount. Is she right?","o":["Yes, they show the same amount","No, 2/8 is bigger","No, 1/4 is bigger","You cannot compare eighths and fourths"],"a":0,"e":"Maya is right! If you split each fourth into 2 pieces, 1 fourth becomes 2 eighths. So 2/8 = 1/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"A shape has ___ equal parts. 3 parts are shaded. The fraction is 3/8. How many equal parts does the shape have?","o":["3","4","8","11"],"a":2,"e":"In 3/8, the bottom number is 8. That means the shape has 8 equal parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ben folds a paper into 2 equal parts and shades 1 part. Mia folds a same-size paper into 4 equal parts and shades 2 parts. Did they shade the same amount?","o":["No, Ben shaded more","No, Mia shaded more","Yes, they shaded the same amount","You cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Ben shaded 1/2. Mia shaded 2/4. These are equal because 2/4 = 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rope is cut into 8 equal pieces. Jess uses 6 pieces. What fraction did she NOT use?","o":["6/8","2/8","8/2","8/6"],"a":1,"e":"She used 6 out of 8 pieces, so 8 - 6 = 2 pieces are left. That is 2/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which two fractions both mean 'half'?","o":["1/2 and 2/4","1/2 and 1/4","2/4 and 2/8","1/4 and 1/8"],"a":0,"e":"1/2 and 2/4 both mean half. 2 out of 4 equal parts is the same as 1 out of 2 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"A sandwich is cut into 4 equal pieces. You eat 3 pieces. What fraction is left?","o":["3/4","1/4","4/4","0/4"],"a":1,"e":"You ate 3 of 4 pieces. 4 - 3 = 1 piece left. That is 1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Rosa splits her brownie into 8 equal pieces. She wants to eat exactly half. How many pieces should she eat?","o":["2 pieces","3 pieces","4 pieces","8 pieces"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8 pieces is 4 pieces. She should eat 4 pieces to eat exactly 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Eli says 4/8 is bigger than 1/2. Is he correct?","o":["Yes, because 4 and 8 are bigger numbers","No, 4/8 and 1/2 are the same","Yes, because eighths are bigger","No, 1/2 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"4/8 = 1/2. They are the same amount. 4 out of 8 equal parts is exactly half.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is split into 8 equal parts. ___ parts are shaded. The fraction shaded is 1/2. What goes in the blank?","o":["1","2","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"1/2 of 8 parts = 4 parts. So 4 parts should be shaded to show 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"A garden has 4 equal sections. 1 section has flowers and 1 section has vegetables. What fraction of the garden is planted?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":1,"e":"1 section of flowers + 1 section of vegetables = 2 sections planted. That is 2 out of 4, or 2/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 1 fourth or 1 eighth?","o":["1 eighth, because 8 > 4","1 fourth, because fewer pieces means bigger pieces","They are the same","You cannot compare them"],"a":1,"e":"1 fourth is bigger. Splitting into 4 pieces gives larger pieces than splitting into 8.","d":"e"},{"t":"A strip of paper is folded into 8 equal parts. 8 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/8","0/8","8/8","8/1"],"a":2,"e":"All 8 out of 8 parts are shaded. That is 8/8, which is 1 whole.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kevin has 2 equal halves of a granola bar. He puts them together. What does he have?","o":["1/2 of a bar","1 whole bar","2 whole bars","1/4 of a bar"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves together = 2/2 = 1 whole granola bar.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pizza has 8 equal slices. Jade eats 3/8 and her mom eats 2/8. What fraction is left? Is more or less than half left?","o":["3/8 left -- less than half","5/8 left -- more than half","3/8 left -- more than half","5/8 left -- less than half"],"a":0,"e":"3/8 + 2/8 = 5/8 eaten. 8/8 - 5/8 = 3/8 left. Half is 4/8, and 3/8 < 4/8, so less than half is left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ravi says 1/8 is bigger than 1/2 because 8 is bigger than 2. What is wrong with Ravi's thinking?","o":["Nothing -- Ravi is correct","More pieces means each piece is smaller, so 1/8 < 1/2","1/8 and 1/2 are equal","You cannot compare fractions with different bottoms"],"a":1,"e":"Ravi is wrong. When you cut into MORE pieces, each piece is SMALLER. 1/8 is much smaller than 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 9 eighths of a cake. Is that more or less than 1 whole cake? By how much?","o":["Less by 1/8","Exactly 1 whole","More by 1/8","More by 2/8"],"a":2,"e":"8/8 = 1 whole. 9/8 = 8/8 + 1/8. So you have 1 whole cake plus 1/8 more.","d":"m"},{"t":"2 kids share 1 pie equally. Then they get a second pie and share it equally too. What fraction of a pie does each kid have now?","o":["1/2 of a pie","1 whole pie","2 halves of a pie","2 whole pies"],"a":1,"e":"Each kid gets 1/2 from the first pie and 1/2 from the second pie. 1/2 + 1/2 = 2/2 = 1 whole pie each.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 8 parts. 3 parts are tall and 5 are short. Can you say 5/8 is shaded if the short parts are colored?","o":["Yes, because 5 of 8 parts are colored","No, because the parts are not all equal","Yes, because most of the parts are colored","No, because you can only shade half"],"a":1,"e":"The parts are not equal (3 tall, 5 short). Fractions require all parts to be the same size, so 5/8 is not correct.","d":"h"},{"t":"Noah shades 2/4 of a square. Eva shades 4/8 of the same size square. Finn shades 1/2 of the same size square. Who shaded the most?","o":["Noah shaded the most","Eva shaded the most","Finn shaded the most","They all shaded the same amount"],"a":3,"e":"2/4 = 1/2 and 4/8 = 1/2. All three fractions are equal -- they all shaded exactly half.","d":"h"},{"t":"4 friends share 3 pies equally. What fraction of a pie does each friend get?","o":["1/4","3/4","4/3","1/3"],"a":1,"e":"3 pies split among 4 friends = 3/4 per friend. Each person gets 3 fourths of a pie.","d":"m"},{"t":"Amara ate 1/4 of a cake on Saturday, 1/4 on Sunday, and 1/4 on Monday. How much has she eaten? How much is left?","o":["3/4 eaten, 1/4 left","3/12 eaten, 9/12 left","2/4 eaten, 2/4 left","3/4 eaten, 3/4 left"],"a":0,"e":"1/4 + 1/4 + 1/4 = 3/4 eaten. The whole cake is 4/4, so 4/4 - 3/4 = 1/4 is left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo says 2/2 is bigger than 4/4 because halves are bigger than fourths. Is Leo right?","o":["Yes, halves are always bigger","No, both equal 1 whole","Yes, because 2 < 4","No, 4/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"Leo is wrong. 2/2 = 1 whole and 4/4 = 1 whole. They are the same amount!","d":"m"},{"t":"A cookie sheet has 8 equal cookies. Mom takes 1/2 of them for a party and Dad takes 1/4 of the total. How many cookies are left?","o":["1 cookie","2 cookies","3 cookies","4 cookies"],"a":1,"e":"Mom takes 1/2 of 8 = 4 cookies. Dad takes 1/4 of 8 = 2 cookies. 4 + 2 = 6 taken. 8 - 6 = 2 cookies left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which list shows fractions from smallest to largest?","o":["1/2, 1/4, 1/8","1/8, 1/2, 1/4","1/8, 1/4, 1/2","1/4, 1/8, 1/2"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 is the smallest piece, then 1/4, then 1/2 is the biggest. More pieces = smaller slices.","d":"e"},{"t":"Kai has 3 fourths of a granola bar. Zoe has 6 eighths of the same size bar. Who has more?","o":["Kai has more","Zoe has more","They have the same amount","You cannot compare them"],"a":2,"e":"3/4 = 6/8 because each fourth splits into 2 eighths. 3 x 2 = 6 eighths. They are equal!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava has 5 halves of a sandwich. How many whole sandwiches can she make? How much is left over?","o":["2 wholes, 1/2 left","5 wholes, nothing left","2 wholes, nothing left","3 wholes, 1/2 left"],"a":0,"e":"2 halves = 1 whole. 4 halves = 2 wholes. The 5th half is left over. So 2 wholes and 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pan of brownies has 8 equal pieces. 3 kids each take 2 pieces. Is there enough for a 4th kid to also take 2 pieces?","o":["Yes, there are 2 left","No, there are 0 left","Yes, there are 3 left","No, there is only 1 left"],"a":0,"e":"3 kids x 2 pieces = 6 pieces taken. 8 - 6 = 2 pieces left. Yes, 1 more kid can take 2 pieces!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ian says if two fractions have the same top number, the one with the bigger bottom number is bigger. Is Ian correct?","o":["Yes, bigger bottom means bigger fraction","No, bigger bottom means smaller pieces so the fraction is smaller","Yes, because more parts is always more","No, they are always equal"],"a":1,"e":"Ian is wrong. With the same top number, a bigger bottom means more pieces, so each piece is smaller. Example: 1/8 < 1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Mia colors 1/2 of a shape red, then 1/4 of the same shape blue. What fraction of the shape is still white?","o":["3/4","1/4","2/4","1/2"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 = 2/4. Red is 2/4 and blue is 1/4. That is 2/4 + 1/4 = 3/4 colored. So 4/4 - 3/4 = 1/4 is white.","d":"h"},{"t":"A ribbon is 1 whole long. You cut off 3/8. Then you cut off another 3/8. How much ribbon is left?","o":["6/8","3/8","2/8","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"3/8 + 3/8 = 6/8 cut off. 8/8 - 6/8 = 2/8 is left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ella says 4/4, 2/2, and 8/8 are all different amounts. Is she right?","o":["Yes, they have different numbers","No, they all equal 1 whole","Yes, 8/8 is the biggest","No, only 4/4 and 2/2 are the same"],"a":1,"e":"Ella is wrong. 4/4 = 1 whole, 2/2 = 1 whole, and 8/8 = 1 whole. When top equals bottom, it is always 1 whole.","d":"h"},{"t":"2 friends want to share 3 granola bars equally. What fraction does each friend get?","o":["3/2 of a bar","2/3 of a bar","1/2 of a bar","1 whole bar"],"a":0,"e":"3 bars shared by 2 friends = 3/2 per friend. That is 1 whole bar and 1/2 more (one and a half bars).","d":"m"},{"t":"Jada says cutting a pizza into 8 slices gives you more pizza than cutting it into 4 slices. What is wrong with her thinking?","o":["Nothing -- she is correct","The total pizza stays the same; more slices just means smaller slices","You actually get less pizza with more cuts","Pizzas can only be cut into 4 slices"],"a":1,"e":"Jada is wrong. Cutting more slices does not create more pizza. The total stays the same -- each slice just gets smaller.","d":"h"}],"quiz":[{"t":"Which fraction is larger: 1/2 or 1/4?","o":["1/2","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"1/2 is larger. Half is a bigger piece than a fourth."},{"t":"A pie has 8 equal slices. Each slice = ?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/6","1/8"],"a":3,"e":"8 equal slices means each slice is 1/8."},{"t":"What does the fraction 3/4 mean?","o":["3 wholes","3 out of 4 equal parts","4 out of 3","3 plus 4"],"a":1,"e":"Numerator 3, denominator 4 = 3 out of 4 equal parts."},{"t":"How many eighths make one whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"8/8 = 1 whole. You need all 8 parts!"},{"t":"Which is smallest: 1/2, 1/4, or 1/8?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","All equal"],"a":2,"e":"More parts = smaller each. 1/8 is smallest piece."},{"t":"Compare: 5/8 and 3/8?","o":["5/8 < 3/8","5/8 > 3/8","5/8 = 3/8","Cannot compare"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 5 > 3, so 5/8 > 3/8."},{"t":"How many fourths make one whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"4/4 = 1 whole."}]},{"points":["SAME denominator? Compare numerators (bigger number = bigger fraction)","SAME numerator? Compare denominators (smaller number = bigger fraction!)","Order fractions from least to greatest or greatest to least"],"examples":[{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Same Denominator","p":"3/8 vs 5/8:","s":"<div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#555;margin:6px 0\">Same size pieces (eighths) — just count the shaded parts!</div><div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#e8f4f8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,21.72 Z\" fill=\"#2980b9\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L78.28,21.72 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#2980b9\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L90.00,50.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,78.28 Z\" fill=\"#2980b9\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">3/8</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#2980b9;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#2980b9\" font-weight=\"bold\">3</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#2980b9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#2980b9\" font-weight=\"bold\">8</text></svg></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><div style=\"font-size:28px;color:#555;align-self:center\">&lt;</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#eafaf1\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,21.72 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L78.28,21.72 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L90.00,50.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,78.28 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L78.28,78.28 A40,40,0,0,1,50.00,90.00 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,90.00 A40,40,0,0,1,21.72,78.28 Z\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">5/8</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#27ae60;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#27ae60\" font-weight=\"bold\">5</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#27ae60\" font-weight=\"bold\">8</text></svg></div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;color:#27ae60\">5/8 is greater! More shaded pieces.</div>","a":"5/8 > 3/8 ✅"},{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Same Numerator","p":"1/2 vs 1/4:","s":"<div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#555;margin:6px 0\">Both have <b>1</b> shaded piece — but the pieces are different sizes!</div><div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,50.00,90.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/2</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">2</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e74c3c;font-size:12px\">bigger piece!</div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><div style=\"font-size:28px;color:#555;align-self:center\">&gt;</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/4</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e67e22;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">4</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e67e22;font-size:12px\">smaller piece</div></div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:13px;color:#555\">Fewer cuts → bigger pieces. Smaller denominator = bigger piece!</div>","a":"1/2 > 1/4 ✅"},{"c":"#8e44ad","tag":"Order from Least","p":"Put in order: 1/4, 1/8, 1/2","s":"<div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:center;align-items:flex-end;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:10px 0\"><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#f3eaf8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,78.28,21.72 Z\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"78.28\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"78.28\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"21.72\" y2=\"21.72\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/8</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#8e44ad;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#8e44ad\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" font-weight=\"bold\">8</text></svg><div style=\"color:#8e44ad;font-size:12px\">smallest</div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><div style=\"font-size:24px;color:#555;align-self:center\">&lt;</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,90.00,50.00 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"90.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"10.00\" y2=\"50.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/4</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e67e22;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e67e22\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e67e22\" font-weight=\"bold\">4</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e67e22;font-size:12px\">medium</div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><div style=\"font-size:24px;color:#555;align-self:center\">&lt;</div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 8px\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M50,50 L50.00,10.00 A40,40,0,0,1,50.00,90.00 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"10.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"50\" y1=\"50\" x2=\"50.00\" y2=\"90.00\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><text x=\"50\" y=\"96\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#555\" font-weight=\"bold\">1/2</text></svg><div style=\"font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;color:#e74c3c;margin-top:4px\"><svg width=\"36\" height=\"52\" viewBox=\"0 0 36 52\" style=\"display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle\"><text x=\"18\" y=\"18\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">1</text><line x1=\"4\" y1=\"27\" x2=\"32\" y2=\"27\" stroke=\"#e74c3c\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><text x=\"18\" y=\"46\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" font-weight=\"bold\">2</text></svg><div style=\"color:#e74c3c;font-size:12px\">largest</div></div></div></div><div style=\"text-align:center;font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;color:#555\">1/8 &lt; 1/4 &lt; 1/2</div>","a":"1/8 < 1/4 < 1/2 ✅"}],"practice":[{"q":"Which is bigger: 3/8 or 5/8?","a":"5/8","h":"Same denominator! 5 pieces is more than 3 pieces.","e":"⚖️"},{"q":"Which is bigger: 1/2 or 1/8?","a":"1/2","h":"Same numerator! Smaller bottom number = bigger piece.","e":"🍕"},{"q":"Compare 2/4 and 2/8","a":"2/4 is bigger","h":"Same numerator. Smaller denominator = bigger pieces!","e":"⚖️"},{"q":"Look at these two fractions. Which is greater: 5/8 or 2/8?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"38\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 38\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg><svg width=\"190\" height=\"38\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 38\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#2980b9\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#2980b9\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg>","a":"5/8","h":"Same denominator! Compare the tops: 5 pieces is more than 2 pieces.","e":"⚖️"},{"q":"Which fraction is smaller: 1/4 or 1/2?<svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,83.0,45.0 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"83.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"7.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,45.0,83.0 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg>","a":"1/4 is smaller","h":"1/4 means cut into MORE pieces, so each piece is SMALLER than 1/2.","e":"⚖️"},{"q":"Put these fractions in order from least to greatest: 1/2, 1/8, 1/4.<svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#f3eaf8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,71.9,18.1 Z\" fill=\"#8e44ad\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"71.9\" y2=\"18.1\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"83.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"71.9\" y2=\"71.9\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"18.1\" y2=\"71.9\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"7.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"18.1\" y2=\"18.1\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#fef3e2\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,83.0,45.0 Z\" fill=\"#e67e22\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"83.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"7.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg><svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#fde8e8\" stroke=\"#aaa\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,45.0,83.0 Z\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"1.2\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.4\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/></svg>","a":"1/8, 1/4, 1/2","h":"More cuts = smaller pieces. 1/8 is smallest, 1/2 is largest!","e":"📊"},{"q":"A pizza is cut into 4 slices. Another pizza is cut into 8 slices. You get 1 slice from each. Which slice is bigger?<svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#F0B27A\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"31\" fill=\"#E74C3C\"/><ellipse cx=\"32\" cy=\"26\" rx=\"8\" ry=\"5\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"57\" cy=\"31\" rx=\"9\" ry=\"5\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"30\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"6\" ry=\"7\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"57\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"7\" ry=\"6\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"45\" cy=\"64\" rx=\"6\" ry=\"4\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><circle cx=\"35\" cy=\"28\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"57\" cy=\"36\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"33\" cy=\"57\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"58\" cy=\"57\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,83.0,45.0 Z\" fill=\"rgba(39,174,96,0.4)\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"83.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"7.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg><svg width=\"90\" height=\"90\" viewBox=\"0 0 90 90\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"#F0B27A\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"31\" fill=\"#E74C3C\"/><ellipse cx=\"32\" cy=\"26\" rx=\"8\" ry=\"5\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"57\" cy=\"31\" rx=\"9\" ry=\"5\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"30\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"6\" ry=\"7\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"57\" cy=\"54\" rx=\"7\" ry=\"6\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><ellipse cx=\"45\" cy=\"64\" rx=\"6\" ry=\"4\" fill=\"#F9E79F\"/><circle cx=\"35\" cy=\"28\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"57\" cy=\"36\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"33\" cy=\"57\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><circle cx=\"58\" cy=\"57\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#922B21\" opacity=\"0.9\"/><path d=\"M45,45 L45.0,7.0 A38,38,0,0,1,71.9,18.1 Z\" fill=\"rgba(39,174,96,0.4)\" stroke=\"#27ae60\" stroke-width=\"1.5\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"7.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"71.9\" y2=\"18.1\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"83.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"71.9\" y2=\"71.9\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"45.0\" y2=\"83.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"18.1\" y2=\"71.9\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"7.0\" y2=\"45.0\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><line x1=\"45\" y1=\"45\" x2=\"18.1\" y2=\"18.1\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"1.8\"/><circle cx=\"45\" cy=\"45\" r=\"38\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#D35400\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg>","a":"1/4 is bigger","h":"Fewer slices means each slice is bigger! 1/4 > 1/8.","e":"🍕"},{"q":"Which fraction is greater: 6/8 or 2/8?<svg width=\"190\" height=\"38\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 38\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#27ae60\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg><svg width=\"190\" height=\"38\" viewBox=\"0 0 190 38\" style=\"display:block;margin:4px auto\"><rect x=\"0.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"23.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#e74c3c\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"47.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"71.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"95.0\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"118.8\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"142.5\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/><rect x=\"166.2\" y=\"0\" width=\"23.8\" height=\"38\" fill=\"#f0e6f8\" stroke=\"#888\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg>","a":"6/8","h":"Same denominator — just compare the numerators. 6 > 2, so 6/8 > 2/8!","e":"⚖️"}],"qBank":[{"t":"3/8 vs 5/8: symbol?","o":["3/8>5/8","3/8<5/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 3<5.","d":"e"},{"t":"1/2 vs 1/4: symbol?","o":["1/2>1/4","1/2<1/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: smaller denominator=bigger piece.","d":"e"},{"t":"Largest: 1/2, 3/8, 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/8","1/2","Equal"],"a":2,"e":"1/2=4/8>3/8.","d":"e"},{"t":"Least to greatest: 1/4, 1/8, 1/2?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"1/8<1/4<1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Same denominator: bigger numerator = ?","o":["Smaller fraction","Bigger fraction","Equal fraction","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Same size pieces: more pieces=bigger fraction.","d":"e"},{"t":"3/4 vs 3/8: symbol?","o":["3/4>3/8","3/4<3/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: smaller denominator=bigger piece.","d":"e"},{"t":"7/8 vs 5/8: symbol?","o":["7/8>5/8","7/8<5/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same denominator: 7>5.","d":"e"},{"t":"1/8 vs 1/4: which is bigger?","o":["1/8","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/4>1/8: fewer pieces=bigger each.","d":"e"},{"t":"5/8 vs 1/2 = 4/8: symbol?","o":["5/8>4/8","5/8<4/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same denominator: 5>4.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/4 vs 1/4: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 2>1.","d":"e"},{"t":"Greatest to least: 3/4, 1/4, 2/4?","o":["3/4,2/4,1/4","1/4,2/4,3/4","2/4,1/4,3/4","3/4,1/4,2/4"],"a":0,"e":"3>2>1 with same denominator.","d":"e"},{"t":"1/3 vs 1/4: which is larger?","o":["1/3","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: 3<4 means 1/3>1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"3/8 vs 3/4: symbol?","o":["3/8>3/4","3/8<3/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same numerator: 8>4 so 3/8<3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Order: 2/8, 5/8, 1/8 least to greatest?","o":["1/8,2/8,5/8","5/8,2/8,1/8","2/8,1/8,5/8","1/8,5/8,2/8"],"a":0,"e":"1<2<5 same denominator.","d":"m"},{"t":"6/8 vs 7/8: symbol?","o":["6/8>7/8","6/8<7/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 6<7.","d":"e"},{"t":"1/4 vs 1/2: which is smaller?","o":["1/4","1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"1/4<1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Same numerator rule: bigger denominator = ?","o":["Bigger fraction","Smaller fraction","Same fraction","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"More pieces means each piece is smaller.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/4 vs 4/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"2/4=1/2 and 4/8=1/2. Equal!","d":"e"},{"t":"3/4 vs 7/8: which is larger?","o":["3/4","7/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"3/4=6/8<7/8.","d":"e"},{"t":"Order greatest to least: 1/8, 1/2, 1/4?","o":["1/2,1/4,1/8","1/8,1/4,1/2","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/2,1/8,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"1/2>1/4>1/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"4/4 vs 8/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"Both equal 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"1/4 vs 2/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"1/4=2/8. Equal!","d":"e"},{"t":"Which helps compare 1/2 and 3/8?","o":["Add them both together","Change to same denominator","Multiply numerators only","Guess which looks bigger"],"a":1,"e":"1/2=4/8. Now compare 4/8 and 3/8: 4>3.","d":"m"},{"t":"5/8 vs 4/4: symbol?","o":["5/8>4/4","5/8<4/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"4/4=1 whole=8/8>5/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"3/8 vs 1/2: symbol?","o":["3/8>1/2","3/8<1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"1/2=4/8>3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/8 vs 1/4 vs 1/2: order smallest to largest?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"Smaller denominator=bigger piece: 1/2 biggest.","d":"m"},{"t":"6/8 vs 3/4: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"6/8=3/4. Equal!","d":"m"},{"t":"7/8 vs 1/2=4/8: symbol?","o":["7/8>1/2","7/8<1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"7>4 same denominator. 7/8>4/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 0?","o":["3/4","1/2","1/8","7/8"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 is the smallest — closest to 0.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 1 whole?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","7/8"],"a":3,"e":"7/8 is the largest — closest to 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is larger: 1/2 or 1/4?","o":["1/4","1/2","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 is larger. When you split something into 2 pieces, each piece is bigger than when you split into 4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is larger: 1/2 or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/2","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 is larger. Splitting into 2 pieces gives much bigger pieces than splitting into 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is larger: 1/4 or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/4","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 is larger. Fewer pieces means each piece is bigger.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is the smallest: 1/2, 1/4, or 1/8?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 is the smallest. When you split into 8 pieces, each piece is very small.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is the largest: 1/2, 1/4, or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"1/2 is the largest. Splitting into only 2 pieces gives the biggest pieces.","d":"m"},{"t":"You get 1/2 of a cookie or 1/8 of the same cookie. Which gives you more cookie?","o":["1/8","1/2","They are the same","It depends on the cookie"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 gives you more. Half a cookie is a lot more than one eighth of a cookie!","d":"h"},{"t":"A pizza is cut into 4 equal slices. Another same-size pizza is cut into 8 equal slices. Which pizza has BIGGER slices?","o":["The one cut into 8 slices","The one cut into 4 slices","Both have the same size slices","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"The pizza cut into 4 slices has bigger slices. Fewer cuts = bigger pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which piece of pie is bigger: 1 fourth or 1 half?","o":["1 fourth","1 half","They are the same","It depends on the pie"],"a":1,"e":"1 half is bigger. A half is a larger piece than a fourth.","d":"e"},{"t":"Sam has 1/4 of a brownie. Ella has 1/2 of the same brownie. Who has more?","o":["Sam","Ella","They have the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Ella has more. 1/2 is a bigger piece than 1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 3/4 or 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/4","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 is bigger. 3 fourths is more than 1 fourth -- it is 3 pieces instead of 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 2/8 or 7/8?","o":["2/8","7/8","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"7/8 is bigger. 7 pieces out of 8 is more than 2 pieces out of 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Would you rather have 1/8 of a cake or 1/2 of the same cake?","o":["1/8, because you get more","1/2, because you get more","They are the same","It depends on the cake"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 gives you much more cake. Half a cake is way bigger than one eighth!","d":"m"},{"t":"2 kids each get 1 piece of pizza. One pizza was cut into 2 slices, the other into 8 slices. Who got a bigger piece?","o":["The kid with a slice from the 8-slice pizza","The kid with a slice from the 2-slice pizza","Both got the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"The kid who got a slice from the 2-slice pizza got 1/2. The other got 1/8. 1/2 > 1/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 5/8 or 2/8?","o":["2/8","5/8","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"5/8 is bigger. When the bottom number is the same, just compare the top numbers: 5 > 2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 1/4 or 3/4?","o":["1/4","3/4","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 is bigger. 3 pieces out of 4 is more than 1 piece out of 4.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ribbon is cut into 8 equal pieces. Is 1 piece bigger or smaller than half the ribbon?","o":["Bigger than half","Smaller than half","Exactly half","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1 piece out of 8 is 1/8. Half the ribbon is 4/8. Since 1/8 < 4/8, one piece is smaller than half.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction shows MORE of a shape: 6/8 or 3/8?","o":["3/8","6/8","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"6/8 shows more. 6 parts shaded out of 8 is more than 3 parts shaded out of 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Mia has 1/2 of a sandwich. Jake has 1/4 of the same sandwich. Who has the smaller piece?","o":["Mia","Jake","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Jake has the smaller piece. 1/4 is smaller than 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is less: 1/8 or 1/4?","o":["1/4","1/8","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/8 is less. More pieces means smaller pieces, so eighths are smaller than fourths.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 4 equal pieces. 2 pieces are cherry and 2 are apple. Which flavor takes up more of the pie?","o":["Cherry","Apple","They take up the same amount","You cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Both flavors have 2 out of 4 pieces. 2/4 = 2/4, so they take up the same amount.","d":"m"},{"t":"Order from smallest to largest: 1/2, 1/8, 1/4.","o":["1/2, 1/4, 1/8","1/8, 1/4, 1/2","1/4, 1/8, 1/2","1/8, 1/2, 1/4"],"a":1,"e":"1/8 is smallest (8 pieces = tiny). 1/4 is next (4 pieces = small). 1/2 is biggest (2 pieces = big).","d":"h"},{"t":"Order from largest to smallest: 1/4, 1/2, 1/8.","o":["1/8, 1/4, 1/2","1/2, 1/4, 1/8","1/4, 1/2, 1/8","1/2, 1/8, 1/4"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 is biggest, then 1/4, then 1/8 is smallest. Fewer pieces = bigger slices.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava gets 3/8 of a pie. Ben gets 5/8 of the same pie. Who gets more?","o":["Ava","Ben","They get the same","You cannot compare"],"a":1,"e":"Both fractions have 8 as the bottom number. 5 > 3, so 5/8 > 3/8. Ben gets more.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is larger: 2/4 or 1/2?","o":["2/4 is larger","1/2 is larger","They are the same","You cannot compare them"],"a":2,"e":"2/4 and 1/2 are equal! 2 out of 4 parts is the same as 1 out of 2 parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"A cake has 8 equal slices. You eat 4 slices. Did you eat more than half, less than half, or exactly half?","o":["More than half","Less than half","Exactly half","You cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8 slices is 4 slices. You ate 4/8, which is exactly 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jess eats 2/8 of a candy bar. Did she eat more or less than 1/4?","o":["More than 1/4","Less than 1/4","Exactly 1/4","You cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"1/4 = 2/8. So Jess ate exactly 1/4 of the candy bar.","d":"h"},{"t":"Who ate more pizza: Maya who ate 3/4, or Eli who ate 6/8?","o":["Maya ate more","Eli ate more","They ate the same amount","You cannot compare"],"a":2,"e":"3/4 = 6/8. They ate the same amount! Each fourth equals 2 eighths, and 3 x 2 = 6.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 1 whole: 3/4, 1/2, or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/2","3/4","They are all the same distance"],"a":2,"e":"3/4 is closest to 1 whole. It is only 1/4 away from a full whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rope is cut into 8 equal pieces. You need more than half. What is the fewest pieces you need to take?","o":["3 pieces","4 pieces","5 pieces","6 pieces"],"a":2,"e":"Half is 4/8. To get MORE than half, you need at least 5 pieces (5/8 > 4/8).","d":"m"},{"t":"Kim has 1/4 of a pie. Lee has 1/4 of a different same-size pie. Together, how much pie do they have?","o":["2/8 of a pie","2/4 of a pie","1/2 of a pie","1/4 of a pie"],"a":1,"e":"Kim has 1/4 and Lee has 1/4. Together that is 1/4 + 1/4 = 2/4 of a pie.","d":"h"},{"t":"Noah says 7/8 is less than 1/2 because eighths are small. Is Noah correct?","o":["Yes, eighths are very small","No, 7/8 is more than 1/2 because 7 eighths is a lot","Yes, any fraction with 8 on the bottom is small","No, 7/8 equals 1/2"],"a":1,"e":"Noah is wrong. 1/2 = 4/8. Since 7/8 > 4/8, we know 7/8 is much MORE than 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 3/8 or 1/2?","o":["3/8","1/2","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 = 4/8. Since 3/8 < 4/8, 1/2 is bigger than 3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Two same-size pizzas are cut differently. Pizza A has 4 equal slices. Pizza B has 8 equal slices. Are 2 slices of Pizza A the same as 4 slices of Pizza B?","o":["No, Pizza A slices are bigger","No, Pizza B slices are more","Yes, both equal 1/2 of a pizza","You cannot compare different pizzas"],"a":2,"e":"2 slices of 4 = 2/4 = 1/2. 4 slices of 8 = 4/8 = 1/2. Yes, they are the same amount!","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is closer to 0: 1/8 or 1/2?","o":["1/2","1/8","They are the same distance","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/8 is closer to 0. It is a very tiny piece, much smaller than 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Put these fractions in order from least to greatest: 7/8, 3/8, 5/8.","o":["7/8, 5/8, 3/8","3/8, 5/8, 7/8","5/8, 3/8, 7/8","3/8, 7/8, 5/8"],"a":1,"e":"All have 8 on the bottom, so compare the tops: 3 < 5 < 7. Order: 3/8, 5/8, 7/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Lina ate 1/2 of her lunch. Ravi ate 3/4 of the same size lunch. Who has more left?","o":["Lina has more left","Ravi has more left","They have the same left","You cannot compare"],"a":0,"e":"Lina ate 1/2 so she has 1/2 left. Ravi ate 3/4 so he has 1/4 left. 1/2 > 1/4, so Lina has more left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Is 4/8 greater than, less than, or equal to 2/4?","o":["Greater than 2/4","Less than 2/4","Equal to 2/4","You cannot compare"],"a":2,"e":"4/8 = 1/2 and 2/4 = 1/2. They are equal!","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 4 equal parts. 3 are shaded. Is more than half shaded?","o":["No, exactly half is shaded","No, less than half is shaded","Yes, more than half is shaded","You cannot tell"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 4 parts is 2 parts. 3 parts are shaded, and 3 > 2, so yes, more than half is shaded.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 2/4 or 3/8?","o":["2/4","3/8","They are equal","You cannot compare"],"a":0,"e":"2/4 = 4/8. Compare 4/8 to 3/8. Since 4 > 3, 2/4 is bigger than 3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Finn has 5/8 of a candy bar. Sam has 3/4 of the same candy bar. Who has more?","o":["Finn","Sam","They have the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 = 6/8. Compare 5/8 to 6/8. Since 6 > 5, Sam has more (6/8 > 5/8).","d":"h"},{"t":"Sam says 1/4 is bigger than 1/2 because 4 is bigger than 2. What should you tell Sam?","o":["You are right, 4 > 2 so 1/4 > 1/2","More parts means smaller pieces, so 1/4 is actually smaller","They are equal","You cannot compare 1/4 and 1/2"],"a":1,"e":"Sam is wrong. Cutting into MORE pieces makes each piece SMALLER. 1/4 < 1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Ella ate 3/8 of a cake. Her brother ate 4/8. How much did they eat together? Is more than half the cake gone?","o":["7/8 -- yes, more than half is gone","7/8 -- no, less than half is gone","7/16 -- yes, more than half","1/8 -- no, less than half"],"a":0,"e":"3/8 + 4/8 = 7/8. Half is 4/8. Since 7/8 > 4/8, yes, way more than half is gone!","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 7 fourths of a pie. How many whole pies is that, and how much extra?","o":["1 whole and 1/4 extra","1 whole and 3/4 extra","2 wholes and 1/4 extra","7 wholes"],"a":1,"e":"4/4 = 1 whole. 7/4 = 4/4 + 3/4 = 1 whole pie and 3/4 extra.","d":"e"},{"t":"A rectangle is cut into 8 parts. 5 parts are wide and 3 parts are narrow. Is 3/8 shaded if the 3 narrow parts are colored?","o":["Yes, because 3 out of 8 are colored","No, because the parts are not all equal","Yes, because narrow parts count","No, because only wide parts count"],"a":1,"e":"The parts are not equal (5 wide, 3 narrow). Fractions need equal parts, so we cannot say 3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"4 kids share 3 pies equally. What fraction of a pie does each kid get?","o":["1/4","3/4","4/3","1/3"],"a":1,"e":"3 pies split among 4 kids = 3/4 per kid. Each child gets 3 fourths of one pie.","d":"e"},{"t":"Order these fractions from smallest to largest: 3/4, 3/8, 1/2.","o":["3/4, 1/2, 3/8","3/8, 1/2, 3/4","1/2, 3/8, 3/4","3/8, 3/4, 1/2"],"a":1,"e":"Convert to eighths: 3/8 = 3/8, 1/2 = 4/8, 3/4 = 6/8. Order: 3/8, 4/8, 6/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kai ate 2/4 of a pizza. Zoe ate 3/8 of the same size pizza. Who ate more?","o":["Kai","Zoe","They ate the same","You cannot compare"],"a":0,"e":"2/4 = 4/8. Compare 4/8 to 3/8. Since 4 > 3, Kai ate more.","d":"h"},{"t":"Mia says 6/8 and 3/4 are different amounts because the numbers are different. Is she right?","o":["Yes, different numbers mean different amounts","No, 6/8 and 3/4 are equal","Yes, 6/8 is bigger","No, 3/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"Mia is wrong. 3/4 = 6/8 because each fourth splits into 2 eighths. They show the same amount.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 8 equal slices. Dad eats 1/4 of the pie and Mom eats 1/2 of the pie. How many slices are left?","o":["1 slice","2 slices","3 slices","4 slices"],"a":1,"e":"Dad eats 1/4 = 2/8 (2 slices). Mom eats 1/2 = 4/8 (4 slices). 2 + 4 = 6 eaten. 8 - 6 = 2 slices left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ben has 5/8 of a candy bar. He says that is more than 1/2 but less than 1 whole. Is he correct?","o":["No, 5/8 is less than 1/2","No, 5/8 equals 1 whole","Yes, 5/8 is between 1/2 and 1 whole","No, 5/8 is more than 1 whole"],"a":2,"e":"1/2 = 4/8 and 1 whole = 8/8. Since 4/8 < 5/8 < 8/8, Ben is correct!","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo says 2/8 is bigger than 1/4 because 2 > 1 and 8 > 4. Is Leo right?","o":["Yes, both numbers are bigger","No, 2/8 and 1/4 are equal","Yes, 2/8 is much bigger","No, 1/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"Leo is wrong! 1/4 = 2/8. They are the same amount. You cannot just compare top and bottom separately.","d":"h"},{"t":"3 friends share 2 cakes equally. What fraction of a cake does each friend get?","o":["1/3","2/3","3/2","1/2"],"a":1,"e":"2 cakes shared among 3 friends = 2/3 per friend. Each gets 2 thirds of a cake.","d":"e"},{"t":"Ava colors 1/2 of a circle red, then 1/4 blue, then 1/8 green. What fraction is still white?","o":["7/8","1/8","3/8","0/8"],"a":1,"e":"In eighths: 1/2 = 4/8, 1/4 = 2/8, 1/8 = 1/8. Total colored: 4 + 2 + 1 = 7/8. White: 8/8 - 7/8 = 1/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Nora has 3 halves of a granola bar. Eli has 5 fourths of a granola bar. Who has more?","o":["Nora, because 3/2 > 5/4","Eli, because 5/4 > 3/2","They have the same","You cannot compare halves and fourths"],"a":0,"e":"3/2 = 6/4. Compare 6/4 to 5/4. Since 6 > 5, Nora has more.","d":"m"},{"t":"A class votes for snacks. 3/8 want chips, 2/8 want fruit, and the rest want pretzels. What fraction wants pretzels? Which snack is most popular?","o":["3/8 pretzels -- pretzels tie with chips for most popular","3/8 pretzels -- chips are most popular","5/8 pretzels -- pretzels are most popular","2/8 pretzels -- chips are most popular"],"a":0,"e":"3/8 + 2/8 = 5/8 accounted for. 8/8 - 5/8 = 3/8 want pretzels. Chips and pretzels tie at 3/8 each.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jada says if you know 1/4 < 1/2, then you also know 3/4 < 3/2. Is she right?","o":["Yes, both comparisons are true","No, 3/4 > 3/2","No, 3/4 = 3/2","You cannot compare those fractions"],"a":0,"e":"Jada is correct! 3/4 = 0.75 and 3/2 = 1.5. Fourths are smaller pieces than halves, so 3 fourths < 3 halves.","d":"h"},{"t":"A garden has 8 equal sections. Tomatoes take 3/8, carrots take 1/4, and flowers take 1/8. What fraction is empty?","o":["5/8","3/8","2/8","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"In eighths: tomatoes 3/8, carrots 1/4 = 2/8, flowers 1/8. Total planted: 3 + 2 + 1 = 6/8. Empty: 8/8 - 6/8 = 2/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is closest to 1 whole without going over: 3/4, 7/8, or 5/8?","o":["3/4","7/8","5/8","They are all the same distance"],"a":1,"e":"In eighths: 3/4 = 6/8, 5/8 = 5/8, 7/8 = 7/8. 7/8 is only 1/8 away from 8/8. That is the closest.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ravi and Mia each have a same-size sandwich. Ravi eats 5/8 of his. Mia eats 3/4 of hers. Who ate more? How much more (in eighths)?","o":["Ravi ate 1/8 more","Mia ate 1/8 more","They ate the same","Mia ate 2/8 more"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 = 6/8. Compare 5/8 and 6/8. Mia ate 6/8 - 5/8 = 1/8 more than Ravi.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ian says 4/8, 2/4, and 1/2 should NOT all be at the same spot on a number line. Is Ian right?","o":["Yes, they have different numbers so different spots","No, they are all equal and belong at the same spot","Yes, 4/8 should be further right","No, but only 2/4 and 1/2 are at the same spot"],"a":1,"e":"Ian is wrong. 4/8 = 2/4 = 1/2. They all equal the same amount and sit at the same point on the number line.","d":"h"}],"quiz":[{"t":"Compare: 3/8 vs 5/8","o":["3/8 > 5/8","3/8 < 5/8","3/8 = 5/8","Cannot compare"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator, compare numerators: 3 < 5. So 3/8 < 5/8."},{"t":"Compare: 1/2 vs 1/4","o":["1/2 > 1/4","1/2 < 1/4","1/2 = 1/4","Cannot compare"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator. Smaller denominator = bigger piece. 2 < 4, so 1/2 > 1/4."},{"t":"Largest fraction: 1/2, 3/8, or 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/8","1/2","All equal"],"a":2,"e":"1/2 = 4/8, which is bigger than 3/8."},{"t":"Order least to greatest: 1/4, 1/8, 1/2","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"Smallest piece first: 1/8 < 1/4 < 1/2."},{"t":"When denominators are the same, the bigger fraction has?","o":["Smaller numerator","Bigger numerator","Any numerator","Zero numerator"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator = compare numerators. Bigger numerator = more pieces = bigger fraction."},{"t":"Which is greater: 3/4 or 3/8?","o":["3/4","3/8","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator (3). Smaller denominator (4 < 8) = bigger pieces. So 3/4 > 3/8."}]}],"unitQuiz":[{"t":"A pizza has 4 equal slices and 1 slice is eaten. What fraction was eaten?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1 of 4 equal slices=1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is larger: 1/2 or 1/4?","o":["1/2","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"1/2>1/4. Half is bigger.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the bottom number of a fraction called?","o":["Numerator","Denominator","Whole","Part"],"a":1,"e":"Denominator=total parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"What does 4/4 equal?","o":["One half","1 whole","Zero parts","2 wholes"],"a":1,"e":"All parts=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ribbon is cut into 8 equal pieces and 3 are used. What fraction of the ribbon is that?","o":["3/5","5/8","3/8","8/3"],"a":2,"e":"3 of 8=3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is smaller: 1/4 or 1/8?","o":["1/4","1/8","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"More pieces=smaller each. 1/8<1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"What does the fraction 1/2 mean?","o":["1 of 4","1 of 2","2 of 1","2 of 2"],"a":1,"e":"1 out of 2 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape has 4 equal parts and 2 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/4","1/2","3/4","2/6"],"a":1,"e":"2 of 4=2/4=1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which list orders 1/4, 1/8, and 1/2 from least to greatest?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"Smallest piece first.","d":"h"},{"t":"What is the top number of a fraction called?","o":["Denominator","Numerator","Whole","Equal"],"a":1,"e":"Numerator=parts you have.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which symbol correctly compares 5/8 and 3/8?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":1,"e":"Same denom,5>3,so 5/8>3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"A square is cut into 2 equal parts. What fraction does each part represent?","o":["1/4","1/3","1/2","2/1"],"a":2,"e":"2 equal parts=each is 1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many fourths are in one whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"4/4=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"For a shape to show fractions, all parts must be what?","o":["Any size","Equal size","Different","3+"],"a":1,"e":"Parts must always be equal.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which symbol correctly compares 1/4 and 1/2?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":0,"e":"1/4<1/2. Larger denom=smaller piece.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pie has 8 equal slices and 2 slices are eaten. What fraction was eaten?","o":["2/10","1/4","2/8","8/2"],"a":2,"e":"2 of 8=2/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"What does the fraction 3/4 mean?","o":["3 whole objects","3 of 4 equal parts","4 of 3 equal parts","3 plus 4 parts"],"a":1,"e":"Numerator 3, denom 4.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many eighths are in one whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"8/8=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which fraction below is equal to 1/2?","o":["2/8","2/4","3/8","3/4"],"a":1,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"A sandwich is cut in half. What fraction does each piece represent?","o":["1/4","1/3","1/2","2/2"],"a":2,"e":"Cut in half=1/2 each.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which number sentence correctly compares 5/8 and 7/8?","o":["5/8>7/8","5/8<7/8","5/8=7/8","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denom,5<7.","d":"h"},{"t":"A rectangle has 8 equal parts and 5 are shaded. What fraction is NOT shaded?","o":["5/8","3/8","5/3","3/5"],"a":1,"e":"8−5=3 parts not shaded. 3 out of 8 = 3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which symbol correctly compares 1/8 and 1/4?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":0,"e":"1/8<1/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"A whole is divided into 4 equal pieces. What fraction does each piece represent?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"4 pieces=each is 1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is the greatest fraction: 1/2, 3/8, or 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/8","1/2","All equal"],"a":2,"e":"1/2=4/8>3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"When the numerator equals the denominator, the fraction equals what?","o":["Zero parts","One half","1 whole","2 wholes"],"a":2,"e":"All parts present=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape has 8 equal parts and 3 are colored. What fraction is colored?","o":["3/5","3/8","8/3","5/8"],"a":1,"e":"3 of 8=3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is cut into 3 parts — two large and one small. Can this show a valid fraction?","o":["Yes, because there are 3 parts","No, all parts must be equal size","Yes, the small piece is 1/3","Yes, any three parts make thirds"],"a":1,"e":"Fractions require all parts to be equal in size.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is larger: 3/4 or 3/8?","o":["3/4","3/8","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator,smaller denom=bigger piece.3/4>3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which number sentence correctly compares 7/8 and 5/8?","o":["7/8>5/8","7/8<5/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same denom,7>5.","d":"h"}],"testBank":[{"t":"Pizza cut into 4 equal slices. Eat 1. Fraction?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1 of 4=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Bottom number of fraction called?","o":["Numerator","Denominator","Whole","Total"],"a":1,"e":"Denominator=total parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"Top number of fraction called?","o":["Denominator","Numerator","Whole","Parts"],"a":1,"e":"Numerator=parts you have.","d":"e"},{"t":"For a shape to show fractions, all parts must be what?","o":["Any size","Equal size","Different","3+"],"a":1,"e":"Always equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"Ribbon in 8 equal pieces, use 3. Fraction?","o":["3/5","5/8","3/8","8/3"],"a":2,"e":"3 of 8=3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"4/4 = ?","o":["Zero parts","One half","1 whole","2 wholes"],"a":2,"e":"All 4 parts=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Circle cut in 2 equal halves. Each part?","o":["1/4","1/3","1/2","2/1"],"a":2,"e":"2 equal parts: each=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Square cut in 8 equal parts. 3 shaded. Fraction?","o":["3/5","3/8","8/3","5/8"],"a":1,"e":"3 of 8=3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What makes a fraction valid?","o":["Many pieces","Equal pieces","At least 3 pieces","Any pieces"],"a":1,"e":"Pieces must be equal.","d":"e"},{"t":"Fraction 2/5 means?","o":["2 wholes of 5","2 out of 5 equal parts","5 out of 2 equal parts","2 groups of 5 objects"],"a":1,"e":"2 parts out of 5 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"Pie cut in 6 equal slices. You eat 2. Fraction?","o":["1/6","2/6","3/6","4/6"],"a":1,"e":"2 of 6=2/6.","d":"m"},{"t":"What does the fraction 1/2 mean?","o":["1 of 4","1 of 2","2 of 1","2 of 2"],"a":1,"e":"1 out of 2 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"Rectangle divided into 5 equal parts. 4 shaded?","o":["1/5","2/5","3/5","4/5"],"a":3,"e":"4 of 5=4/5.","d":"e"},{"t":"When the numerator equals the denominator, the fraction equals what?","o":["Zero parts","One half","1 whole","2 wholes"],"a":2,"e":"All parts present=whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"8 equal parts, 1 colored. Fraction?","o":["1/8","8/1","1/4","1/2"],"a":0,"e":"1 of 8=1/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"3 of 4 parts shaded. Fraction?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/3"],"a":2,"e":"3 of 4=3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Denominator 6 means?","o":["6 pieces colored","6 equal parts total","6+something","None"],"a":1,"e":"Denominator=total equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"Fraction for \"half\"?","o":["2/1","1/2","2/2","1/4"],"a":1,"e":"Half=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Candy bar split in 3 equal pieces, eat 1. Fraction?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","3/1"],"a":1,"e":"1 of 3=1/3.","d":"e"},{"t":"5/5 = ?","o":["5 halves","1 whole","5 wholes","1/5"],"a":1,"e":"5 of 5=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Shape divided in 4 parts — 2 are equal, 2 are not. Valid fraction?","o":["Yes","No","Maybe","Depends"],"a":1,"e":"Parts must ALL be equal for a valid fraction.","d":"m"},{"t":"Numerator of 3/7?","o":["7","3","10","4"],"a":1,"e":"Top number=3=numerator.","d":"e"},{"t":"Denominator of 5/8?","o":["5","8","13","3"],"a":1,"e":"Bottom number=8=denominator.","d":"e"},{"t":"6 equal parts, 6 colored. Fraction = ?","o":["0/6","1/6","6/6","6/0"],"a":2,"e":"All 6 colored=6/6=1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is a fraction?","o":["3+4","7-2","2/5","3×1"],"a":2,"e":"2/5 is a fraction.","d":"e"},{"t":"Fraction for \"three fourths\"?","o":["3/7","4/3","3/4","7/3"],"a":2,"e":"Three fourths=3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Watermelon cut into 8 equal slices, 3 eaten. Left?","o":["3/8","5/8","8/5","8/3"],"a":1,"e":"8-3=5 left. 5/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"4 parts, 1 shaded. Fraction?","o":["4/1","1/4","1/1","4/4"],"a":1,"e":"1 of 4=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many thirds in 1 whole?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":1,"e":"3/3=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"10 equal parts, 7 colored. Fraction?","o":["7/10","10/7","3/10","10/3"],"a":0,"e":"7 of 10=7/10.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is larger: 1/2 or 1/4?","o":["1/2","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"1/2>1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"A pie has 8 equal slices. Each slice=?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/6","1/8"],"a":3,"e":"8 equal slices: each=1/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"What does the fraction 3/4 mean?","o":["3 whole objects","3 of 4 equal parts","4 of 3 equal parts","3 plus 4 parts"],"a":1,"e":"3 out of 4 equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"How many eighths are in one whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"8/8=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Smallest piece: 1/2, 1/4, or 1/8?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","All equal"],"a":2,"e":"More parts=smaller each. 1/8 smallest.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which symbol correctly compares 5/8 and 3/8?","o":["5/8<3/8","5/8>3/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 5>3.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many fourths are in one whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"4/4=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Halves in one whole?","o":["1","2","3","4"],"a":1,"e":"2/2=1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/4 equals?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","3/4"],"a":2,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"4/8 equals?","o":["1/4","1/3","1/2","3/4"],"a":2,"e":"4/8=1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Pizza: 4 slices total, you ate 2. Fraction eaten?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/2"],"a":1,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Rectangle: 8 parts, 4 shaded. Fraction?","o":["1/8","2/8","3/8","4/8"],"a":3,"e":"4/8=1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"3/8 is?","o":["3 wholes and 8 parts","3 parts out of 8","8 parts out of 3","3 plus 8 parts"],"a":1,"e":"3 of 8 equal parts.","d":"m"},{"t":"More than half: 3/4 or 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/4","Equal","Neither"],"a":1,"e":"3/4>1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is closest to 1 whole?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","3/4"],"a":3,"e":"3/4 is largest — closest to 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"7/8 means how many parts shaded?","o":["1","7","8","15"],"a":1,"e":"7 out of 8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Fold paper in 4 equal parts, color 1. Fraction colored?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","4/1"],"a":2,"e":"1 of 4=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/8 is same as?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","3/8"],"a":1,"e":"2/8=1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which shows one half?","o":["2/4","1/4","3/4","2/8"],"a":0,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Bar split in 8 equal parts, 6 colored. Fraction?","o":["5/8","6/8","7/8","8/6"],"a":1,"e":"6/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Less than half: 1/8, 3/4, 1/2, 5/8?","o":["3/4","5/8","1/2","1/8"],"a":3,"e":"1/8<1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Circle divided into 4. 3 parts colored. Fraction?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/3"],"a":2,"e":"3/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"5/8 + 3/8 = ?","o":["7/8","8/8","1 whole","8/16"],"a":2,"e":"5+3=8. 8/8=1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which is half of 1/2?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/3","1/6"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 1/2=1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Shade 3/8 of 8 equal parts. How many colored?","o":["2","3","4","5"],"a":1,"e":"3 out of 8=3 colored.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/4 + 1/4 = ?","o":["1/4","1/2","3/4","1"],"a":1,"e":"1+1=2 fourths=2/4=1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"5/8 − 2/8 = ?","o":["2/8","3/8","4/8","5/8"],"a":1,"e":"5-2=3. 3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"4/4 − 1/4 = ?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":2,"e":"4-1=3. 3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"2/8 + 4/8 = ?","o":["4/8","6/8","8/8","10/8"],"a":1,"e":"2+4=6. 6/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/2 of 8 = ?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8=4.","d":"m"},{"t":"3/8 vs 5/8: symbol?","o":["3/8>5/8","3/8<5/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 3<5.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/2 vs 1/4: symbol?","o":["1/2>1/4","1/2<1/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: smaller denominator=bigger piece.","d":"m"},{"t":"Largest: 1/2, 3/8, 1/4?","o":["1/4","3/8","1/2","Equal"],"a":2,"e":"1/2=4/8>3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Least to greatest: 1/4, 1/8, 1/2?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"1/8<1/4<1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Same denominator: bigger numerator = ?","o":["Smaller fraction","Bigger fraction","Equal fraction","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Same size pieces: more pieces=bigger fraction.","d":"e"},{"t":"3/4 vs 3/8: symbol?","o":["3/4>3/8","3/4<3/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: smaller denominator=bigger piece.","d":"m"},{"t":"7/8 vs 5/8: symbol?","o":["7/8>5/8","7/8<5/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same denominator: 7>5.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/8 vs 1/4: which is bigger?","o":["1/8","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/4>1/8: fewer pieces=bigger each.","d":"m"},{"t":"5/8 vs 1/2 = 4/8: symbol?","o":["5/8>4/8","5/8<4/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"Same denominator: 5>4.","d":"m"},{"t":"2/4 vs 1/4: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 2>1.","d":"m"},{"t":"Greatest to least: 3/4, 1/4, 2/4?","o":["3/4,2/4,1/4","1/4,2/4,3/4","2/4,1/4,3/4","3/4,1/4,2/4"],"a":0,"e":"3>2>1 with same denominator.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/3 vs 1/4: which is larger?","o":["1/3","1/4","Equal","Cannot tell"],"a":0,"e":"Same numerator: 3<4 means 1/3>1/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"3/8 vs 3/4: symbol?","o":["3/8>3/4","3/8<3/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same numerator: 8>4 so 3/8<3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"Order: 2/8, 5/8, 1/8 least to greatest?","o":["1/8,2/8,5/8","5/8,2/8,1/8","2/8,1/8,5/8","1/8,5/8,2/8"],"a":0,"e":"1<2<5 same denominator.","d":"h"},{"t":"6/8 vs 7/8: symbol?","o":["6/8>7/8","6/8<7/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"Same denominator: 6<7.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/4 vs 1/2: which is smaller?","o":["1/4","1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"1/4<1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"Same numerator rule: bigger denominator = ?","o":["Bigger fraction","Smaller fraction","Same fraction","Cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"More pieces means each piece is smaller.","d":"e"},{"t":"2/4 vs 4/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"2/4=1/2 and 4/8=1/2. Equal!","d":"m"},{"t":"3/4 vs 7/8: which is larger?","o":["3/4","7/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"3/4=6/8<7/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Order greatest to least: 1/8, 1/2, 1/4?","o":["1/2,1/4,1/8","1/8,1/4,1/2","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/2,1/8,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"1/2>1/4>1/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"4/4 vs 8/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"Both equal 1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/4 vs 2/8: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"1/4=2/8. Equal!","d":"m"},{"t":"Which helps compare 1/2 and 3/8?","o":["Add them both together","Change to same denominator","Multiply numerators only","Guess which looks bigger"],"a":1,"e":"1/2=4/8. Now compare 4/8 and 3/8: 4>3.","d":"h"},{"t":"5/8 vs 4/4: symbol?","o":["5/8>4/4","5/8<4/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"4/4=1 whole=8/8>5/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"3/8 vs 1/2: symbol?","o":["3/8>1/2","3/8<1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":1,"e":"1/2=4/8>3/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"1/8 vs 1/4 vs 1/2: order smallest to largest?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"Smaller denominator=bigger piece: 1/2 biggest.","d":"h"},{"t":"6/8 vs 3/4: symbol?","o":["<",">","=","x"],"a":2,"e":"6/8=3/4. Equal!","d":"m"},{"t":"7/8 vs 1/2=4/8: symbol?","o":["7/8>1/2","7/8<1/2","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"7>4 same denominator. 7/8>4/8.","d":"m"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 0?","o":["3/4","1/2","1/8","7/8"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 is the smallest — closest to 0.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 1 whole?","o":["1/8","1/4","1/2","7/8"],"a":3,"e":"7/8 is the largest — closest to 1.","d":"e"},{"t":"Pizza: 4 equal slices, eat 1. Fraction?","o":["1/2","1/3","1/4","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which fraction is larger: 1/2 or 1/4?","o":["1/2","1/4","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"1/2.","d":"m"},{"t":"What is the bottom number of a fraction called?","o":["Numerator","Denominator","Whole","Part"],"a":1,"e":"Denominator.","d":"e"},{"t":"What does 4/4 equal?","o":["One half","1 whole","Zero parts","2 wholes"],"a":1,"e":"1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ribbon is cut into 8 equal pieces and 3 are used. What fraction of the ribbon is that?","o":["3/5","5/8","3/8","8/3"],"a":2,"e":"3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Smallest: 1/2,1/4,1/8?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","Equal"],"a":2,"e":"1/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many fourths are in one whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"4/4=1.","d":"e"},{"t":"4 parts,2 shaded. Fraction?","o":["1/4","1/2","3/4","2/6"],"a":1,"e":"2/4=1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"Order least-greatest: 1/4,1/8,1/2?","o":["1/8,1/4,1/2","1/2,1/4,1/8","1/4,1/8,1/2","1/8,1/2,1/4"],"a":0,"e":"1/8<1/4<1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"3/4 vs 3/8. Larger?","o":["3/4","3/8","Equal","Cannot"],"a":0,"e":"3/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is split into 2 equal parts. What is each part called?","o":["A fourth","A half","An eighth","A whole"],"a":1,"e":"When something is divided into 2 equal parts, each part is called a half.","d":"e"},{"t":"A rectangle is cut into 4 equal parts. 3 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/4","3/4","4/3","3/3"],"a":1,"e":"3 out of 4 equal parts are shaded. That is 3/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many halves make 1 whole?","o":["1","2","4","8"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves put together make 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is larger: 1/2 or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/2","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 is larger. When you cut into only 2 pieces, each piece is much bigger than cutting into 8.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 8 equal slices. 5 slices are gone. What fraction is left?","o":["5/8","3/8","8/5","8/3"],"a":1,"e":"5 slices are gone, so 8 - 5 = 3 slices are left. That is 3/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"What does the bottom number in a fraction tell you?","o":["How many parts are shaded","How many equal parts in all","How big the whole is","How many shapes there are"],"a":1,"e":"The bottom number tells how many equal parts the whole is divided into.","d":"e"},{"t":"A square is split into 4 equal parts. All 4 parts are shaded. What fraction is shaded?","o":["1/4","4/4","0/4","4/1"],"a":1,"e":"All 4 out of 4 parts are shaded. That is 4/4, which equals 1 whole.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many eighths make 1 whole?","o":["2","4","6","8"],"a":3,"e":"It takes 8 eighths to make 1 whole. 8/8 = 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 1/4 or 1/8?","o":["1/8","1/4","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 is bigger. Fewer pieces means each piece is larger.","d":"h"},{"t":"In the fraction 5/8, what does the 5 mean?","o":["There are 5 equal parts in all","We are counting 5 of the parts","There are 5 shapes","Each part is size 5"],"a":1,"e":"The top number 5 tells us we are counting 5 of the 8 equal parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"A cookie is split into 2 equal parts. You eat 1 part. What fraction is left?","o":["1/2","2/2","0/2","2/1"],"a":0,"e":"You ate 1 of 2 parts. 2 - 1 = 1 part is left. That is 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 6/8 or 2/8?","o":["2/8","6/8","They are the same","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"6/8 is bigger. Both have 8 equal parts, but 6 pieces is more than 2 pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"A candy bar is split into 8 equal pieces. 1 piece is eaten. What fraction was eaten?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","8/1"],"a":2,"e":"1 out of 8 equal pieces was eaten. That is 1/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"What must be true to write a fraction?","o":["The parts must be different sizes","The parts must be equal","The shape must be round","There must be exactly 2 parts"],"a":1,"e":"To write a fraction, the whole must be split into equal parts.","d":"e"},{"t":"A ribbon is cut into 4 equal parts. 2 parts are blue. What fraction is blue?","o":["2/4","4/2","1/4","2/2"],"a":0,"e":"2 out of 4 equal parts are blue. That is 2/4.","d":"m"},{"t":"How many fourths make 1 whole?","o":["2","3","4","8"],"a":2,"e":"It takes 4 fourths (4/4) to make 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pizza has 8 equal slices. 0 slices are taken. What fraction is taken?","o":["8/8","0/8","1/8","8/0"],"a":1,"e":"No slices are taken. 0 out of 8 = 0/8. That means none.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is the smallest piece: 1/2, 1/4, or 1/8?","o":["1/2","1/4","1/8","They are all the same"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 is the smallest. Cutting into 8 pieces makes tiny pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"A waffle is cut into 4 equal parts. You eat 1 part. What fraction is left?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":2,"e":"You ate 1 of 4 parts. 4 - 1 = 3 parts left. That is 3/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"A paper is folded into 8 equal parts. 4 are colored red. What fraction is red?","o":["4/8","8/4","4/4","1/4"],"a":0,"e":"4 out of 8 equal parts are red. That is 4/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"A shape is split into 4 parts but the parts are NOT equal. Can we write a fraction for the shaded part? Why?","o":["Yes, because something is shaded","No, because fractions need equal parts","Yes, because there are 4 parts","No, because there are too many parts"],"a":1,"e":"Fractions only work when the parts are equal. If the parts are different sizes, we cannot write a fraction.","d":"m"},{"t":"Order from smallest to largest: 1/2, 1/8, 1/4.","o":["1/2, 1/4, 1/8","1/8, 1/4, 1/2","1/4, 1/8, 1/2","1/8, 1/2, 1/4"],"a":1,"e":"1/8 is smallest (tiny pieces), then 1/4, then 1/2 is biggest. More cuts = smaller pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"A brownie is cut into 8 equal pieces. You eat 3 pieces. What fraction is LEFT?","o":["3/8","5/8","8/3","8/5"],"a":1,"e":"You ate 3 of 8. That leaves 8 - 3 = 5 pieces, or 5/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jake says the fraction 3/4 means 4 out of 3 equal parts. Is Jake correct?","o":["Yes","No, it means 3 out of 4 equal parts","No, it means 3 plus 4","Yes, the bigger number always goes on top"],"a":1,"e":"3/4 means 3 out of 4 equal parts. The top is how many we count; the bottom is how many equal parts in all.","d":"h"},{"t":"Anna shades 2/4 of a circle. Marco shades 1/2 of the same size circle. Who shaded more?","o":["Anna","Marco","They shaded the same amount","You cannot compare them"],"a":2,"e":"2/4 = 1/2. They shaded the same amount!","d":"h"},{"t":"A pie is cut into 8 slices. Is 3/8 more or less than half the pie?","o":["More than half","Less than half","Exactly half","You cannot tell"],"a":1,"e":"Half of 8 slices is 4 slices (4/8). Since 3 < 4, 3/8 is less than half.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which two fractions are BOTH equal to 1 whole?","o":["1/2 and 2/4","2/2 and 4/4","1/4 and 1/8","3/4 and 4/8"],"a":1,"e":"2/2 = 1 whole and 4/4 = 1 whole. When top equals bottom, it is always 1 whole.","d":"e"},{"t":"A pizza has 4 equal slices. You eat some and 1/4 is left. How many slices did you eat?","o":["1 slice","2 slices","3 slices","4 slices"],"a":2,"e":"1/4 left means 1 of 4 slices remains. So you ate 4 - 1 = 3 slices.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 5/8 or 3/8?","o":["3/8","5/8","They are equal","You cannot compare"],"a":1,"e":"Same bottom number, so compare tops: 5 > 3. 5/8 is bigger.","d":"h"},{"t":"Eli splits a cracker into 2 pieces but one piece is way bigger. He says each piece is 1/2. Is Eli correct?","o":["Yes, there are 2 pieces","No, the pieces must be equal to call them halves","Yes, any 2 pieces are halves","No, crackers cannot be split into fractions"],"a":1,"e":"Eli is wrong. For halves, the 2 pieces must be equal in size.","d":"h"},{"t":"How many eighths equal 1/2?","o":["2","3","4","6"],"a":2,"e":"Half of 8 is 4. So 4/8 = 1/2.","d":"e"},{"t":"A shape has ___ equal parts. 5 parts are shaded. The fraction is 5/8. What goes in the blank?","o":["5","8","3","13"],"a":1,"e":"In 5/8, the bottom number is 8. The shape has 8 equal parts.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which fraction is closest to 1 whole: 3/4, 1/2, or 1/4?","o":["1/4","1/2","3/4","They are all the same distance"],"a":2,"e":"3/4 is closest to 1 whole. It is only 1/4 away from being complete.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rope is cut into 8 equal pieces. Ava uses 6 pieces. What fraction did she NOT use?","o":["6/8","2/8","8/6","8/2"],"a":1,"e":"She used 6 of 8. 8 - 6 = 2 are unused. That is 2/8.","d":"h"},{"t":"Rosa says 4/8 is bigger than 1/2. Is she right?","o":["Yes, because 4 and 8 are bigger numbers","No, 4/8 equals 1/2","Yes, eighths are bigger","No, 1/2 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"4/8 and 1/2 are the same. 4 out of 8 equal parts is exactly half.","d":"h"},{"t":"A garden has 4 equal sections. 1 has flowers and 2 have vegetables. What fraction is planted?","o":["1/4","2/4","3/4","4/4"],"a":2,"e":"1 flowers + 2 vegetables = 3 sections planted. That is 3/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"Which is bigger: 2/4 or 3/8?","o":["2/4","3/8","They are equal","You cannot compare"],"a":0,"e":"2/4 = 4/8. Since 4/8 > 3/8, 2/4 is bigger.","d":"h"},{"t":"A circle is divided into 8 equal parts. How many parts must you shade to show 1/4?","o":["1 part","2 parts","4 parts","8 parts"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 of 8 = 2 parts. So shade 2 out of 8 parts to show 1/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kai has 2 equal halves of a granola bar. He puts them together. What does he have?","o":["1/2 of a bar","1 whole bar","2 whole bars","2/4 of a bar"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves = 2/2 = 1 whole granola bar.","d":"m"},{"t":"Sam says 1/4 is bigger than 1/2 because 4 is bigger than 2. Is Sam correct? Why not?","o":["Yes, 4 > 2 so 1/4 > 1/2","No, more pieces means smaller pieces so 1/4 < 1/2","They are equal","You cannot compare different fractions"],"a":1,"e":"Sam is wrong. More pieces means SMALLER pieces. 1/4 is smaller than 1/2.","d":"h"},{"t":"Emma ate 2/8 of a pizza. Jake ate 3/8. How much did they eat together? Is more than half gone?","o":["5/8 -- yes, more than half is gone","5/8 -- no, less than half","5/16 -- yes, more than half","6/8 -- yes, more than half"],"a":0,"e":"2/8 + 3/8 = 5/8. Half is 4/8. Since 5/8 > 4/8, yes, more than half is gone.","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 5 fourths of a pie. Is that more or less than 1 whole pie? How much more?","o":["Less by 1/4","Exactly 1 whole","More by 1/4","More by 2/4"],"a":2,"e":"4/4 = 1 whole. 5/4 = 4/4 + 1/4. That is 1 whole plus 1/4 more.","d":"m"},{"t":"A rectangle is split into 6 parts. 2 parts are big and 4 are small. Can you say 4/6 is shaded if the 4 small parts are colored?","o":["Yes, 4 of 6 parts are colored","No, the parts are not equal so we cannot write a fraction","Yes, most parts are colored","No, you can only use halves, fourths, and eighths"],"a":1,"e":"The parts are not equal. Fractions require equal-sized parts, so 4/6 is not correct here.","d":"h"},{"t":"3 friends share 2 pies equally. What fraction does each friend get?","o":["1/3","2/3","3/2","1/2"],"a":1,"e":"2 pies shared among 3 friends = 2/3 per friend.","d":"m"},{"t":"Order from smallest to largest: 3/4, 3/8, 1/2.","o":["3/4, 1/2, 3/8","3/8, 1/2, 3/4","1/2, 3/8, 3/4","3/8, 3/4, 1/2"],"a":1,"e":"In eighths: 3/8 = 3/8, 1/2 = 4/8, 3/4 = 6/8. So 3/8 < 1/2 < 3/4.","d":"h"},{"t":"A pan of brownies has 8 equal pieces. Mom eats 1/8, Dad eats 2/8, and you eat 3/8. What fraction is left for your brother?","o":["6/8","3/8","2/8","1/8"],"a":2,"e":"1/8 + 2/8 + 3/8 = 6/8 eaten. 8/8 - 6/8 = 2/8 left for your brother.","d":"h"},{"t":"Liam says 8/8 is bigger than 4/4 because 8 > 4. Is he right?","o":["Yes, 8 is bigger than 4","No, both equal 1 whole","Yes, eighths add up to more","No, 4/4 is bigger"],"a":1,"e":"8/8 = 1 whole and 4/4 = 1 whole. They are the same amount!","d":"h"},{"t":"Ava splits a candy bar into 8 equal pieces. She gives 1/2 to her friend. How many pieces did she give?","o":["1 piece","2 pieces","4 pieces","8 pieces"],"a":2,"e":"1/2 of 8 = 4 pieces. She gave 4 of the 8 equal pieces.","d":"h"},{"t":"Mia colors 1/2 of a shape red, then 1/4 blue. What fraction is still white?","o":["3/4","1/4","2/4","1/2"],"a":1,"e":"1/2 = 2/4. Red + blue = 2/4 + 1/4 = 3/4 colored. 4/4 - 3/4 = 1/4 is white.","d":"h"},{"t":"Kai has 3/4 of a bar. Zoe has 6/8 of the same size bar. Who has more?","o":["Kai","Zoe","They have the same","You cannot compare"],"a":2,"e":"3/4 = 6/8. They have the same amount!","d":"h"},{"t":"You have 3 halves of a sandwich. How many whole sandwiches is that?","o":["1 whole","1 whole and 1 half","2 wholes","3 wholes"],"a":1,"e":"2 halves = 1 whole. 3 halves = 1 whole + 1/2 left over.","d":"e"},{"t":"A cookie sheet has 8 equal cookies. Mom takes 1/4 and Dad takes 1/2. How many cookies are left?","o":["1 cookie","2 cookies","3 cookies","4 cookies"],"a":1,"e":"Mom takes 1/4 of 8 = 2 cookies. Dad takes 1/2 of 8 = 4 cookies. 2 + 4 = 6 taken. 8 - 6 = 2 left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Leo says 2/8 is bigger than 1/4 because 2 > 1. Is Leo right?","o":["Yes, 2 > 1 so 2/8 > 1/4","No, they are equal","Yes, eighths are bigger than fourths","No, 1/4 is much bigger"],"a":1,"e":"1/4 = 2/8. They are equal! You cannot just compare top numbers when the bottoms are different.","d":"h"},{"t":"4 kids share 3 cookies equally. What fraction of a cookie does each kid get?","o":["1/4","3/4","4/3","1/3"],"a":1,"e":"3 cookies split among 4 kids = 3/4 per kid.","d":"m"},{"t":"Nora says fractions can never be bigger than 1 whole. Is she correct?","o":["Yes, fractions are always less than 1","No, fractions like 5/4 are more than 1 whole","Yes, the top number must be smaller","No, but only halves can be more than 1"],"a":1,"e":"Nora is wrong. 5/4, 3/2, 9/8 are all bigger than 1 whole. The top CAN be bigger than the bottom.","d":"m"},{"t":"A ribbon is 1 whole long. You cut off 3/8 and then another 2/8. What fraction is left?","o":["5/8","3/8","1/8","6/8"],"a":1,"e":"3/8 + 2/8 = 5/8 cut off. 8/8 - 5/8 = 3/8 is left.","d":"h"},{"t":"Ian says if two fractions have the same top number, the one with the bigger bottom is bigger. Is he right?","o":["Yes, bigger bottom means more","No, bigger bottom means smaller pieces so less overall","Yes, because more parts is always more","It depends on the numbers"],"a":1,"e":"Ian is wrong. Same top number but bigger bottom = smaller pieces. Example: 1/8 < 1/4.","d":"e"},{"t":"Which is closest to 1 whole without going over: 3/4, 7/8, or 1/2?","o":["3/4","7/8","1/2","They are all the same distance"],"a":1,"e":"In eighths: 1/2 = 4/8, 3/4 = 6/8, 7/8 = 7/8. 7/8 is just 1/8 away from 1 whole. That is closest.","d":"h"},{"t":"Jada says cutting a pizza into 8 slices gives you more pizza than cutting it into 4 slices. What is wrong with her thinking?","o":["Nothing, she is correct","The total amount stays the same -- more slices just means smaller slices","You get less pizza with more cuts","Pizzas can only be cut into 4 slices"],"a":1,"e":"Jada is wrong. Cutting more slices does not create more pizza. The total stays the same; each slice just gets smaller.","d":"h"},{"t":"8 cookies are shared equally among 2 friends. How many cookies does each friend get?","o":["4","2","8","6"],"a":0,"e":"Share equally: 8÷2=4. Each friend gets 4 cookies!"}]});
